var book = {
	"name": "Luke",
	"numChapters": 24,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>Inasmuch as many have undertaken to compile an account of the things <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24895A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24895A\"></sup>accomplished among us,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>just as they were handed down to us by those who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24896B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24896B\"></sup>from the beginning were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24896C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24896C\"></sup>eyewitnesses and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24896D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24896D\"></sup>servants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24896E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24896E\"></sup>the word,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>it seemed fitting for me as well, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24897F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24897F\"></sup>having investigated everything carefully from the beginning, to write <i>it</i> out for you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24897G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24897G\"></sup>in consecutive order, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24897H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24897H\"></sup>most excellent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24897I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24897I\"></sup>Theophilus;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>so that you may know the exact truth about the things you have been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24898J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24898J\"></sup>taught.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24899K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24899K\"></sup>In the days of Herod, king of Judea, there was a priest named Zacharias, of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24899L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24899L\"></sup>division of Abijah; and he had a wife from the daughters of Aaron, and her name was Elizabeth.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They were both <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24900M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24900M\"></sup>righteous in the sight of God, walking <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24900N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24900N\"></sup>blamelessly in all the commandments and requirements of the Lord.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But they had no child, because Elizabeth was barren, and they were both advanced in years.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now it happened <i>that</i> while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24902O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24902O\"></sup>he was performing his priestly service before God in the <i>appointed</i> order of his division,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>according to the custom of the priestly office, he was chosen by lot <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24903P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24903P\"></sup>to enter the temple of the Lord and burn incense.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the whole multitude of the people were in prayer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24904Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24904Q\"></sup>outside at the hour of the incense offering.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24905R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24905R\"></sup>an angel of the Lord appeared to him, standing to the right of the altar of incense.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Zacharias was troubled when he saw <i>the angel</i>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24906S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24906S\"></sup>fear gripped him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But the angel said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24907T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24907T\"></sup>Do not be afraid, Zacharias, for your petition has been heard, and your wife Elizabeth will bear you a son, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24907U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24907U\"></sup>you will give him the name John.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You will have joy and gladness, and many will rejoice at his birth.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For he will be great in the sight of the Lord; and he will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24909V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24909V\"></sup>drink no wine or liquor, and he will be filled with the Holy Spirit while yet in his mother’s womb.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24910W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24910W\"></sup>turn many of the sons of Israel back to the Lord their God.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>It is he who will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24911X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24911X\"></sup>go <i>as a forerunner</i> before Him in the spirit and power of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24911Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24911Y\"></sup>Elijah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24911Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24911Z\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">to turn the hearts of the fathers back to the children</span>, and the disobedient to the attitude of the righteous, so as to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24911AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24911AA\"></sup>make ready a people prepared for the Lord.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Zacharias said to the angel, “How will I know this <i>for certain</i>? For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24912AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24912AB\"></sup>I am an old man and my wife is advanced in years.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The angel answered and said to him, “I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24913AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24913AC\"></sup>Gabriel, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24913AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24913AD\"></sup>stands in the presence of God, and I have been sent to speak to you and to bring you this good news.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And behold, you shall be silent and unable to speak until the day when these things take place, because you did not believe my words, which will be fulfilled in their proper time.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The people were waiting for Zacharias, and were wondering at his delay in the temple.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But when he came out, he was unable to speak to them; and they realized that he had seen a vision in the temple; and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24916AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24916AE\"></sup>kept making signs to them, and remained mute.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When the days of his priestly service were ended, he went back home.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>After these days Elizabeth his wife became pregnant, and she kept herself in seclusion for five months, saying,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“This is the way the Lord has dealt with me in the days when He looked <i>with favor</i> upon <i>me</i>, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24919AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24919AF\"></sup>take away my disgrace among men.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now in the sixth month the angel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24920AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24920AG\"></sup>Gabriel was sent from God to a city in Galilee called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24920AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24920AH\"></sup>Nazareth,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24921AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24921AI\"></sup>a virgin engaged to a man whose name was Joseph, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24921AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24921AJ\"></sup>of the descendants of David; and the virgin’s name was Mary.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And coming in, he said to her, “Greetings, favored one! The Lord <i>is</i> with you.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But she <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24923AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24923AK\"></sup>was very perplexed at <i>this</i> statement, and kept pondering what kind of salutation this was.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The angel said to her, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24924AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24924AL\"></sup>Do not be afraid, Mary; for you have found favor with God.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And behold, you will conceive in your womb and bear a son, and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24925AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24925AM\"></sup>shall name Him Jesus.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He will be great and will be called the Son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24926AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24926AN\"></sup>the Most High; and the Lord God will give Him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24926AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24926AO\"></sup>the throne of His father David;",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24927AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24927AP\"></sup>and He will reign over the house of Jacob forever, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24927AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24927AQ\"></sup>and His kingdom will have no end.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Mary said to the angel, “How can this be, since I am a virgin?”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The angel answered and said to her, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24929AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24929AR\"></sup>The Holy Spirit will come upon you, and the power of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24929AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24929AS\"></sup>the Most High will overshadow you; and for that reason <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24929AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24929AT\"></sup>the holy Child shall be called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24929AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24929AU\"></sup>the Son of God.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And behold, even your relative Elizabeth has also conceived a son in her old age; and she who was called barren is now in her sixth month.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24931AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24931AV\"></sup>nothing will be impossible with God.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And Mary said, “Behold, the bondslave of the Lord; may it be done to me according to your word.” And the angel departed from her.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Now at this time Mary arose and went in a hurry to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24933AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24933AW\"></sup>the hill country, to a city of Judah,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>and entered the house of Zacharias and greeted Elizabeth.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>When Elizabeth heard Mary’s greeting, the baby leaped in her womb; and Elizabeth was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24935AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24935AX\"></sup>filled with the Holy Spirit.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And she cried out with a loud voice and said, “Blessed <i>are</i> you among women, and blessed <i>is</i> the fruit of your womb!",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And how has it <i>happened</i> to me, that the mother of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24937AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24937AY\"></sup>my Lord would come to me?",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>For behold, when the sound of your greeting reached my ears, the baby leaped in my womb for joy.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24939AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24939AZ\"></sup>blessed <i>is</i> she who believed that there would be a fulfillment of what had been spoken to her by the Lord.”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>And Mary said:“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24940BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24940BA\"></sup>My soul <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24940BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24940BB\"></sup>exalts the Lord,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24941BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24941BC\"></sup>my spirit has rejoiced in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24941BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24941BD\"></sup>God my Savior.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>“For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24942BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24942BE\"></sup>He has had regard for the humble state of His bondslave;For behold, from this time on all generations will count me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24942BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24942BF\"></sup>blessed.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>“For the Mighty One has done great things for me;And holy is His name.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24944BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24944BG\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">And His mercy is</span> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">upon generation after generation</span><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Toward those who fear Him</span>.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24945BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24945BH\"></sup>He has done mighty deeds with His arm;He has scattered <i>those who were</i> proud in the thoughts of their heart.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>“He has brought down rulers from <i>their</i> thrones,And has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24946BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24946BI\"></sup>exalted those who were humble.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24947BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24947BJ\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">He has filled the hungry with good things</span>;And sent away the rich empty-handed.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>“He has given help to Israel His servant,In remembrance of His mercy,",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24949BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24949BK\"></sup>As He spoke to our fathers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24949BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24949BL\"></sup>To Abraham and his descendants forever.”",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>And Mary stayed with her about three months, and <i>then</i> returned to her home.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>Now the time had come for Elizabeth to give birth, and she gave birth to a son.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>Her neighbors and her relatives heard that the Lord had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24952BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24952BM\"></sup>displayed His great mercy toward her; and they were rejoicing with her.",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>And it happened that on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24953BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24953BN\"></sup>the eighth day they came to circumcise the child, and they were going to call him Zacharias, after his father.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>But his mother answered and said, “No indeed; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24954BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24954BO\"></sup>he shall be called John.”",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>And they said to her, “There is no one among your relatives who is called by that name.”",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>And they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24956BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24956BP\"></sup>made signs to his father, as to what he wanted him called.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>And he asked for a tablet and wrote as follows, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24957BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24957BQ\"></sup>His name is John.” And they were all astonished.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24958BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24958BR\"></sup>And at once his mouth was opened and his tongue <i>loosed</i>, and he <i>began</i> to speak in praise of God.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>Fear came on all those living around them; and all these matters were being talked about in all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24959BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24959BS\"></sup>the hill country of Judea.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>All who heard them kept them in mind, saying, “What then will this child <i>turn out to</i> be?” For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24960BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24960BT\"></sup>the hand of the Lord was certainly with him.",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>And his father Zacharias <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24961BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24961BU\"></sup>was filled with the Holy Spirit, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24961BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24961BV\"></sup>prophesied, saying:",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24962BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24962BW\"></sup>Blessed <i>be</i> the Lord God of Israel,For He has visited us and accomplished <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24962BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24962BX\"></sup>redemption for His people,",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>And has raised up a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24963BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24963BY\"></sup>horn of salvation for usIn the house of David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24963BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24963BZ\"></sup>His servant—",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24964CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24964CA\"></sup>As He spoke by the mouth of His holy prophets <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24964CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24964CB\"></sup>from of old—",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24965CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24965CC\"></sup>Salvation <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24965CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24965CD\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">from our enemies</span>,And <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">from the hand of all who hate us</span>;",
			"72": "<sup class=\"versenum\">72 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24966CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24966CE\"></sup>To show mercy toward our fathers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24966CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24966CF\"></sup>And to remember His holy covenant,",
			"73": "<sup class=\"versenum\">73 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24967CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24967CG\"></sup>The oath which He swore to Abraham our father,",
			"74": "<sup class=\"versenum\">74 </sup>To grant us that we, being rescued from the hand of our enemies,Might serve Him without fear,",
			"75": "<sup class=\"versenum\">75 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24969CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24969CH\"></sup>In holiness and righteousness before Him all our days.",
			"76": "<sup class=\"versenum\">76 </sup>“And you, child, will be called the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24970CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24970CI\"></sup>prophet of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24970CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24970CJ\"></sup>the Most High;For you will go on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24970CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24970CK\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">before the Lord to</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24970CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24970CL\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">prepare His ways</span>;",
			"77": "<sup class=\"versenum\">77 </sup>To give to His people <i>the</i> knowledge of salvationBy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24971CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24971CM\"></sup>the forgiveness of their sins,",
			"78": "<sup class=\"versenum\">78 </sup>Because of the tender mercy of our God,With which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24972CN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CN&quot;&gt;CN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24972CN\"></sup>the Sunrise from on high will visit us,",
			"79": "<sup class=\"versenum\">79 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24973CO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CO&quot;&gt;CO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24973CO\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">To shine upon those who sit in darkness and the shadow of death</span>,To guide our feet into the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24973CP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CP&quot;&gt;CP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24973CP\"></sup>way of peace.”",
			"80": "<sup class=\"versenum\">80 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24974CQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CQ&quot;&gt;CQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24974CQ\"></sup>And the child continued to grow and to become strong in spirit, and he lived in the deserts until the day of his public appearance to Israel."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Now in those days a decree went out from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24975A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24975A\"></sup>Caesar Augustus, that a census be taken of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24975B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24975B\"></sup>all the inhabited earth.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>This was the first census taken while Quirinius was governor of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24976C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24976C\"></sup>Syria.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And everyone was on his way to register for the census, each to his own city.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Joseph also went up from Galilee, from the city of Nazareth, to Judea, to the city of David which is called Bethlehem, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24978D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24978D\"></sup>he was of the house and family of David,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>in order to register along with Mary, who was engaged to him, and was with child.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>While they were there, the days were completed for her to give birth.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And she <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24981E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24981E\"></sup>gave birth to her firstborn son; and she wrapped Him in cloths, and laid Him in a manger, because there was no room for them in the inn.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In the same region there were <i>some</i> shepherds staying out in the fields and keeping watch over their flock by night.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24983F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24983F\"></sup>an angel of the Lord suddenly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24983G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24983G\"></sup>stood before them, and the glory of the Lord shone around them; and they were terribly frightened.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But the angel said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24984H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24984H\"></sup>Do not be afraid; for behold, I bring you good news of great joy which will be for all the people;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>for today in the city of David there has been born for you a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24985I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24985I\"></sup>Savior, who is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24985J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24985J\"></sup>Christ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24985K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24985K\"></sup>the Lord.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24986L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24986L\"></sup>This <i>will be</i> a sign for you: you will find a baby wrapped in cloths and lying in a manger.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And suddenly there appeared with the angel a multitude of the heavenly host praising God and saying,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24988M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24988M\"></sup>Glory to God in the highest,And on earth peace among men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24988N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24988N\"></sup>with whom He is pleased.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the angels had gone away from them into heaven, the shepherds <i>began</i> saying to one another, “Let us go straight to Bethlehem then, and see this thing that has happened which the Lord has made known to us.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So they came in a hurry and found their way to Mary and Joseph, and the baby as He lay in the manger.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When they had seen this, they made known the statement which had been told them about this Child.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And all who heard it wondered at the things which were told them by the shepherds.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But Mary <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24993O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24993O\"></sup>treasured all these things, pondering them in her heart.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The shepherds went back, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24994P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24994P\"></sup>glorifying and praising God for all that they had heard and seen, just as had been told them.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24995Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24995Q\"></sup>eight days had passed, before His circumcision, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24995R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24995R\"></sup>His name was <i>then</i> called Jesus, the name given by the angel before He was conceived in the womb.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24996S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24996S\"></sup>And when the days for their purification according to the law of Moses were completed, they brought Him up to Jerusalem to present Him to the Lord",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>(as it is written in the Law of the Lord, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24997T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24997T\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Every</span> <i>firstborn</i> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">male that opens the womb shall be called holy to the Lord</span>”),",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and to offer a sacrifice according to what was said in the Law of the Lord, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24998U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24998U\"></sup>A <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">pair of turtledoves or two young pigeons</span>.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And there was a man in Jerusalem whose name was Simeon; and this man was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24999V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24999V\"></sup>righteous and devout, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24999W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24999W\"></sup>looking for the consolation of Israel; and the Holy Spirit was upon him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25000X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25000X\"></sup>it had been revealed to him by the Holy Spirit that he would not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25000Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25000Y\"></sup>see death before he had seen the Lord’s Christ.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And he came in the Spirit into the temple; and when the parents brought in the child Jesus, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25001Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25001Z\"></sup>to carry out for Him the custom of the Law,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>then he took Him into his arms, and blessed God, and said,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Now Lord, You are releasing Your bond-servant to depart in peace,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25003AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25003AA\"></sup>According to Your word;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>For my eyes have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25004AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25004AB\"></sup>seen Your salvation,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Which You have prepared in the presence of all peoples,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25006AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25006AC\"></sup>A <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Light</span> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">of revelation to the Gentiles</span>,And the glory of Your people Israel.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And His father and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25007AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25007AD\"></sup>mother were amazed at the things which were being said about Him.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And Simeon blessed them and said to Mary <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25008AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25008AE\"></sup>His mother, “Behold, this <i>Child</i> is appointed for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25008AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25008AF\"></sup>the fall and rise of many in Israel, and for a sign to be opposed—",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>and a sword will pierce even your own soul—to the end that thoughts from many hearts may be revealed.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And there was a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25010AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25010AG\"></sup>prophetess, Anna the daughter of Phanuel, of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25010AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25010AH\"></sup>the tribe of Asher. She was advanced in years <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25010AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25010AI\"></sup>and had lived with <i>her</i> husband seven years after her marriage,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>and then as a widow to the age of eighty-four. She never left the temple, serving night and day with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25011AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25011AJ\"></sup>fastings and prayers.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>At that very moment she came up and <i>began</i> giving thanks to God, and continued to speak of Him to all those who were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25012AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25012AK\"></sup>looking for the redemption of Jerusalem.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>When they had performed everything according to the Law of the Lord, they returned to Galilee, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25013AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25013AL\"></sup>their own city of Nazareth.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25014AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25014AM\"></sup>The Child continued to grow and become strong, increasing in wisdom; and the grace of God was upon Him.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Now His parents went to Jerusalem every year at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25015AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25015AN\"></sup>the Feast of the Passover.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And when He became twelve, they went up <i>there</i> according to the custom of the Feast;",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>and as they were returning, after spending the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25017AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25017AO\"></sup>full number of days, the boy Jesus stayed behind in Jerusalem. But His parents were unaware of it,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>but supposed Him to be in the caravan, and went a day’s journey; and they <i>began</i> looking for Him among their relatives and acquaintances.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>When they did not find Him, they returned to Jerusalem looking for Him.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Then, after three days they found Him in the temple, sitting in the midst of the teachers, both listening to them and asking them questions.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>And all who heard Him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25021AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25021AP\"></sup>were amazed at His understanding and His answers.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>When they saw Him, they were astonished; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25022AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25022AQ\"></sup>His mother said to Him, “Son, why have You treated us this way? Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25022AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25022AR\"></sup>Your father and I have been anxiously looking for You.”",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Why is it that you were looking for Me? Did you not know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25023AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25023AS\"></sup>I had to be in My Father’s <i>house</i>?”</span>",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25024AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25024AT\"></sup>they did not understand the statement which He had made to them.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>And He went down with them and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25025AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25025AU\"></sup>Nazareth, and He continued in subjection to them; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25025AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25025AV\"></sup>His mother <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25025AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25025AW\"></sup>treasured all <i>these</i> things in her heart.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>And Jesus kept increasing in wisdom and stature, and in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25026AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25026AX\"></sup>favor with God and men."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Now in the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar, when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25027A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25027A\"></sup>Pontius Pilate was governor of Judea, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25027B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25027B\"></sup>Herod was tetrarch of Galilee, and his brother Philip was tetrarch of the region of Ituraea and Trachonitis, and Lysanias was tetrarch of Abilene,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>in the high priesthood of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25028C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25028C\"></sup>Annas and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25028D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25028D\"></sup>Caiaphas, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25028E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25028E\"></sup>the word of God came to John, the son of Zacharias, in the wilderness.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he came into all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25029F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25029F\"></sup>the district around the Jordan, preaching a baptism of repentance for the forgiveness of sins;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>as it is written in the book of the words of Isaiah the prophet,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25030G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25030G\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">The voice of one crying in the wilderness</span>,‘<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Make ready the way of the Lord</span>,<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Make His paths straight</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25031H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25031H\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Every ravine will be filled</span>,<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">And every mountain and hill will be</span> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">brought low</span>;<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">The crooked will become straight</span>,<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">And the rough roads smooth</span>;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25032I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25032I\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">And all</span> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">flesh will</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25032J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25032J\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">see the salvation of God</span>.’”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So he <i>began</i> saying to the crowds who were going out to be baptized by him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25033K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25033K\"></sup>You brood of vipers, who warned you to flee from the wrath to come?",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Therefore bear fruits in keeping with repentance, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25034L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25034L\"></sup>do not begin to say to yourselves, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25034M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25034M\"></sup>We have Abraham for our father,’ for I say to you that from these stones God is able to raise up children to Abraham.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Indeed the axe is already laid at the root of the trees; so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25035N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25035N\"></sup>every tree that does not bear good fruit is cut down and thrown into the fire.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the crowds were questioning him, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25036O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25036O\"></sup>Then what shall we do?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he would answer and say to them, “The man who has two tunics is to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25037P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25037P\"></sup>share with him who has none; and he who has food is to do likewise.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And <i>some</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25038Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25038Q\"></sup>tax collectors also came to be baptized, and they said to him, “Teacher, what shall we do?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And he said to them, “Collect no more than what you have been ordered to.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><i>Some</i> soldiers were questioning him, saying, “And <i>what about</i> us, what shall we do?” And he said to them, “Do not take money from anyone by force, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25040R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25040R\"></sup>accuse <i>anyone</i> falsely, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25040S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25040S\"></sup>be content with your wages.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now while the people were in a state of expectation and all were wondering in their hearts about John, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25041T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25041T\"></sup>as to whether he was the Christ,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25042U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25042U\"></sup>John answered and said to them all, “As for me, I baptize you with water; but One is coming who is mightier than I, and I am not fit to untie the thong of His sandals; He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and fire.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>His <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25043V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25043V\"></sup>winnowing fork is in His hand to thoroughly clear His threshing floor, and to gather the wheat into His barn; but He will burn up the chaff with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25043W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25043W\"></sup>unquenchable fire.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So with many other exhortations he preached the gospel to the people.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25045X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25045X\"></sup>Herod the tetrarch was reprimanded by him because of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25045Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25045Y\"></sup>Herodias, his brother’s wife, and because of all the wicked things which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25045Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25045Z\"></sup>Herod had done,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Herod also added this to them all: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25046AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25046AA\"></sup>he locked John up in prison.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25047AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25047AB\"></sup>Now when all the people were baptized, Jesus was also baptized, and while He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25047AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25047AC\"></sup>praying, heaven was opened,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and the Holy Spirit descended upon Him in bodily form like a dove, and a voice came out of heaven, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25048AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25048AD\"></sup>You are My beloved Son, in You I am well-pleased.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25049AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25049AE\"></sup>When He began His ministry, Jesus Himself was about thirty years of age, being, as was supposed, the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25049AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25049AF\"></sup>Joseph, the son of Eli,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>the son of Matthat, the son of Levi, the son of Melchi, the son of Jannai, the son of Joseph,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>the son of Mattathias, the son of Amos, the son of Nahum, the son of Hesli, the son of Naggai,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>the son of Maath, the son of Mattathias, the son of Semein, the son of Josech, the son of Joda,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>the son of Joanan, the son of Rhesa, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25053AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25053AG\"></sup>the son of Zerubbabel, the son of Shealtiel, the son of Neri,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>the son of Melchi, the son of Addi, the son of Cosam, the son of Elmadam, the son of Er,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>the son of Joshua, the son of Eliezer, the son of Jorim, the son of Matthat, the son of Levi,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>the son of Simeon, the son of Judah, the son of Joseph, the son of Jonam, the son of Eliakim,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>the son of Melea, the son of Menna, the son of Mattatha, the son of Nathan, the son of David,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25058AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25058AH\"></sup>the son of Jesse, the son of Obed, the son of Boaz, the son of Salmon, the son of Nahshon,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>the son of Amminadab, the son of Admin, the son of Ram, the son of Hezron, the son of Perez, the son of Judah,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>the son of Jacob, the son of Isaac, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25060AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25060AI\"></sup>the son of Abraham, the son of Terah, the son of Nahor,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>the son of Serug, the son of Reu, the son of Peleg, the son of Heber, the son of Shelah,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>the son of Cainan, the son of Arphaxad, the son of Shem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25062AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25062AJ\"></sup>the son of Noah, the son of Lamech,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>the son of Methuselah, the son of Enoch, the son of Jared, the son of Mahalaleel, the son of Cainan,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>the son of Enosh, the son of Seth, the son of Adam, the son of God."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25065A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25065A\"></sup>Jesus, full of the Holy Spirit, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25065B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25065B\"></sup>returned from the Jordan and was led around by the Spirit in the wilderness",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25066C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25066C\"></sup>forty days, being tempted by the devil. And He ate nothing during those days, and when they had ended, He became hungry.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And the devil said to Him, “If You are the Son of God, tell this stone to become bread.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Jesus answered him, <span class=\"woj\">“It is written, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25068D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25068D\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Man shall not live on bread alone</span>.’”</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25069E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25069E\"></sup>And he led Him up and showed Him all the kingdoms of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25069F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25069F\"></sup>the world in a moment of time.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the devil said to Him, “I will give You all this domain and its glory; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25070G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25070G\"></sup>for it has been handed over to me, and I give it to whomever I wish.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Therefore if You worship before me, it shall all be Yours.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Jesus answered him, <span class=\"woj\">“It is written, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25072H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25072H\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">You shall worship the Lord your God and serve Him only</span>.’”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25073I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25073I\"></sup>And he led Him to Jerusalem and had Him stand on the pinnacle of the temple, and said to Him, “If You are the Son of God, throw Yourself down from here;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>for it is written,‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25074J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25074J\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">He will command His angels concerning You to guard You</span>,’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and,‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25075K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25075K\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">On</span> <i>their</i> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">hands they will bear You up</span>,<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">So that You will not strike Your foot against a stone</span>.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Jesus answered and said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“It is said, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25076L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25076L\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">You shall not put the Lord your God to the test</span>.’”</span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When the devil had finished every temptation, he left Him until an opportune time.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25078M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25078M\"></sup>Jesus returned to Galilee in the power of the Spirit, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25078N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25078N\"></sup>news about Him spread through all the surrounding district.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And He <i>began</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25079O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25079O\"></sup>teaching in their synagogues and was praised by all.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And He came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25080P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25080P\"></sup>Nazareth, where He had been brought up; and as was His custom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25080Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25080Q\"></sup>He entered the synagogue on the Sabbath, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25080R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25080R\"></sup>stood up to read.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the book of the prophet Isaiah was handed to Him. And He opened the book and found the place where it was written,",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25082S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25082S\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">The Spirit of the Lord is upon Me</span>,</span><span class=\"woj\"><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Because He anointed Me to preach the gospel to the poor</span>.</span><span class=\"woj\"><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">He has sent Me to proclaim release to the captives</span>,</span><span class=\"woj\"><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">And recovery of sight to the blind</span>,</span><span class=\"woj\"><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">To set free those who are oppressed</span>,</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25083T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25083T\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">To proclaim the favorable year of the Lord</span>.”</span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25084U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25084U\"></sup>closed the book, gave it back to the attendant and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25084V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25084V\"></sup>sat down; and the eyes of all in the synagogue were fixed on Him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And He began to say to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Today this Scripture has been fulfilled in your hearing.”</span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And all were speaking well of Him, and wondering at the gracious words which were falling from His lips; and they were saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25086W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25086W\"></sup>Is this not Joseph’s son?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“No doubt you will quote this proverb to Me, ‘Physician, heal yourself! Whatever we heard was done <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25087X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25087X\"></sup>at Capernaum, do here in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25087Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25087Y\"></sup>your hometown as well.’”</span>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And He said, <span class=\"woj\">“Truly I say to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25088Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25088Z\"></sup>no prophet is welcome in his hometown.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But I say to you in truth, there were many widows in Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25089AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25089AA\"></sup>in the days of Elijah, when the sky was shut up for three years and six months, when a great famine came over all the land;</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and yet Elijah was sent to none of them, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25090AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25090AB\"></sup>only to Zarephath, <i>in the land</i> of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25090AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25090AC\"></sup>Sidon, to a woman who was a widow.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And there were many lepers in Israel in the time of Elisha the prophet; and none of them was cleansed, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25091AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25091AD\"></sup>only Naaman the Syrian.”</span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And all <i>the people</i> in the synagogue were filled with rage as they heard these things;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and they got up and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25093AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25093AE\"></sup>drove Him out of the city, and led Him to the brow of the hill on which their city had been built, in order to throw Him down the cliff.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25094AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25094AF\"></sup>passing through their midst, He went His way.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25095AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25095AG\"></sup>He came down to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25095AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25095AH\"></sup>Capernaum, a city of Galilee, and He was teaching them on the Sabbath;",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25096AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25096AI\"></sup>they were amazed at His teaching, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25096AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25096AJ\"></sup>His message was with authority.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>In the synagogue there was a man possessed by the spirit of an unclean demon, and he cried out with a loud voice,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Let us alone! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25098AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25098AK\"></sup>What business do we have with each other, Jesus of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25098AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25098AL\"></sup>Nazareth? Have You come to destroy us? I know who You are—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25098AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25098AM\"></sup>the Holy One of God!”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But Jesus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25099AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25099AN\"></sup>rebuked him, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“Be quiet and come out of him!”</span> And when the demon had thrown him down in the midst <i>of the people</i>, he came out of him without doing him any harm.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And amazement came upon them all, and they <i>began</i> talking with one another saying, “What is this message? For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25100AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25100AO\"></sup>with authority and power He commands the unclean spirits and they come out.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25101AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25101AP\"></sup>the report about Him was spreading into every locality in the surrounding district.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25102AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25102AQ\"></sup>Then He got up and <i>left</i> the synagogue, and entered Simon’s home. Now Simon’s mother-in-law was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25102AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25102AR\"></sup>suffering from a high fever, and they asked Him to help her.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And standing over her, He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25103AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25103AS\"></sup>rebuked the fever, and it left her; and she immediately got up and waited on them.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25104AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25104AT\"></sup>While <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25104AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25104AU\"></sup>the sun was setting, all those who had any <i>who were</i> sick with various diseases brought them to Him; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25104AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25104AV\"></sup>laying His hands on each one of them, He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25104AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25104AW\"></sup>healing them.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Demons also were coming out of many, shouting, “You are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25105AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25105AX\"></sup>the Son of God!” But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25105AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25105AY\"></sup>rebuking them, He would <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25105AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25105AZ\"></sup>not allow them to speak, because they knew Him to be the Christ.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25106BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25106BA\"></sup>When day came, Jesus left and went to a secluded place; and the crowds were searching for Him, and came to Him and tried to keep Him from going away from them.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>But He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“I must preach the kingdom of God to the other cities also, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25107BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25107BB\"></sup>for I was sent for this purpose.”</span>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>So He kept on preaching in the synagogues <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25108BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25108BC\"></sup>of Judea."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25109A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25109A\"></sup>Now it happened that while the crowd was pressing around Him and listening to the word of God, He was standing by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25109B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25109B\"></sup>the lake of Gennesaret;",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and He saw two boats lying at the edge of the lake; but the fishermen had gotten out of them and were washing their nets.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25111C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25111C\"></sup>He got into one of the boats, which was Simon’s, and asked him to put out a little way from the land. And He sat down and <i>began</i> teaching the people from the boat.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When He had finished speaking, He said to Simon, <span class=\"woj\">“Put out into the deep water and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25112D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25112D\"></sup>let down your nets for a catch.”</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Simon answered and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25113E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25113E\"></sup>Master, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25113F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25113F\"></sup>we worked hard all night and caught nothing, but I will do as You say <i>and</i> let down the nets.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When they had done this, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25114G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25114G\"></sup>they enclosed a great quantity of fish, and their nets <i>began</i> to break;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>so they signaled to their partners in the other boat for them to come and help them. And they came and filled both of the boats, so that they began to sink.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But when Simon Peter saw <i>that</i>, he fell down at Jesus’ feet, saying, “Go away from me Lord, for I am a sinful man!”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For amazement had seized him and all his companions because of the catch of fish which they had taken;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and so also <i>were</i> James and John, sons of Zebedee, who were partners with Simon. And Jesus said to Simon, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25118H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25118H\"></sup>Do not fear, from now on you will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25118I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25118I\"></sup>catching men.”</span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When they had brought their boats to land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25119J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25119J\"></sup>they left everything and followed Him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25120K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25120K\"></sup>While He was in one of the cities, behold, <i>there was</i> a man covered with leprosy; and when he saw Jesus, he fell on his face and implored Him, saying, “Lord, if You are willing, You can make me clean.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And He stretched out His hand and touched him, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“I am willing; be cleansed.”</span> And immediately the leprosy left him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And He ordered him to tell no one, <span class=\"woj\">“But go and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25122L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25122L\"></sup>show yourself to the priest and make an offering for your cleansing, just as Moses commanded, as a testimony to them.”</span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25123M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25123M\"></sup>the news about Him was spreading even farther, and large crowds were gathering to hear <i>Him</i> and to be healed of their sicknesses.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But Jesus Himself would <i>often</i> slip away to the wilderness and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25124N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25124N\"></sup>pray.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>One day He was teaching; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25125O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25125O\"></sup>there were <i>some</i> Pharisees and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25125P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25125P\"></sup>teachers of the law sitting <i>there</i>, who had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25125Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25125Q\"></sup>come from every village of Galilee and Judea and <i>from</i> Jerusalem; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25125R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25125R\"></sup>the power of the Lord was <i>present</i> for Him to perform healing.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25126S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25126S\"></sup>And <i>some</i> men <i>were</i> carrying on a bed a man who was paralyzed; and they were trying to bring him in and to set him down in front of Him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But not finding any <i>way</i> to bring him in because of the crowd, they went up on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25127T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25127T\"></sup>the roof and let him down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25127U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25127U\"></sup>through the tiles with his stretcher, into the middle <i>of the crowd</i>, in front of Jesus.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Seeing their faith, He said, <span class=\"woj\">“Friend, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25128V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25128V\"></sup>your sins are forgiven you.”</span>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The scribes and the Pharisees <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25129W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25129W\"></sup>began to reason, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25129X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25129X\"></sup>Who is this <i>man</i> who speaks blasphemies? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25129Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25129Y\"></sup>Who can forgive sins, but God alone?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But Jesus, aware of their reasonings, answered and said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Why are you reasoning in your hearts?</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Which is easier, to say, ‘Your sins have been forgiven you,’ or to say, ‘Get up and walk’?</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But, so that you may know that the Son of Man has authority on earth to forgive sins,”</span>—He said to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25132Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25132Z\"></sup>paralytic—<span class=\"woj\">“I say to you, get up, and pick up your stretcher and go home.”</span>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Immediately he got up before them, and picked up what he had been lying on, and went home <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25133AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25133AA\"></sup>glorifying God.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They were all struck with astonishment and <i>began</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25134AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25134AB\"></sup>glorifying God; and they were filled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25134AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25134AC\"></sup>with fear, saying, “We have seen remarkable things today.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25135AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25135AD\"></sup>After that He went out and noticed a tax collector named <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25135AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25135AE\"></sup>Levi sitting in the tax booth, and He said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Follow Me.”</span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25136AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25136AF\"></sup>left everything behind, and got up and <i>began</i> to follow Him.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25137AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25137AG\"></sup>Levi gave a big reception for Him in his house; and there was a great crowd of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25137AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25137AH\"></sup>tax collectors and other <i>people</i> who were reclining <i>at the table</i> with them.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25138AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25138AI\"></sup>The Pharisees and their scribes <i>began</i> grumbling at His disciples, saying, “Why do you eat and drink with the tax collectors and sinners?”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And Jesus answered and said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25139AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25139AJ\"></sup><i>It is</i> not those who are well who need a physician, but those who are sick.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>I have not come to call the righteous but sinners to repentance.”</span>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And they said to Him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25141AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25141AK\"></sup>The disciples of John often fast and offer prayers, the <i>disciples</i> of the Pharisees also do the same, but Yours eat and drink.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“You cannot make the attendants of the bridegroom fast while the bridegroom is with them, can you?</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25143AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25143AL\"></sup>But <i>the</i> days will come; and when the bridegroom is taken away from them, then they will fast in those days.”</span>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And He was also telling them a parable: <span class=\"woj\">“No one tears a piece of cloth from a new garment and puts it on an old garment; otherwise he will both tear the new, and the piece from the new will not match the old.</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And no one puts new wine into old wineskins; otherwise the new wine will burst the skins and it will be spilled out, and the skins will be ruined.</span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>But new wine must be put into fresh wineskins.</span>",
			"39": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And no one, after drinking old <i>wine</i> wishes for new; for he says, ‘The old is good <i>enough</i>.’”</span>"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25148A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25148A\"></sup>Now it happened that He was passing through <i>some</i> grainfields on a Sabbath; and His disciples <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25148B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25148B\"></sup>were picking the heads of grain, rubbing them in their hands, and eating <i>the grain</i>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But some of the Pharisees said, “Why do you do what <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25149C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25149C\"></sup>is not lawful on the Sabbath?”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Jesus answering them said, <span class=\"woj\">“Have you not even read <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25150D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25150D\"></sup>what David did when he was hungry, he and those who were with him,</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>how he entered the house of God, and took and ate the consecrated bread which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25151E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25151E\"></sup>is not lawful for any to eat except the priests alone, and gave it to his companions?”</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And He was saying to them, <span class=\"woj\">“The Son of Man is Lord of the Sabbath.”</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25153F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25153F\"></sup>On another Sabbath He entered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25153G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25153G\"></sup>the synagogue and was teaching; and there was a man there whose right hand was withered.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The scribes and the Pharisees <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25154H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25154H\"></sup>were watching Him closely <i>to see</i> if He healed on the Sabbath, so that they might find <i>reason</i> to accuse Him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25155I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25155I\"></sup>knew what they were thinking, and He said to the man with the withered hand, <span class=\"woj\">“Get up and come forward!”</span> And he got up and came forward.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“I ask you, is it lawful to do good or to do harm on the Sabbath, to save a life or to destroy it?”</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>After <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25157J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25157J\"></sup>looking around at them all, He said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Stretch out your hand!”</span> And he did <i>so</i>; and his hand was restored.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But they themselves were filled with rage, and discussed together what they might do to Jesus.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>It was at this time that He went off to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25159K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25159K\"></sup>the mountain to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25159L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25159L\"></sup>pray, and He spent the whole night in prayer to God.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And when day came, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25160M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25160M\"></sup>He called His disciples to Him and chose twelve of them, whom He also named as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25160N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25160N\"></sup>apostles:",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Simon, whom He also named Peter, and Andrew his brother; and James and John; and Philip and Bartholomew;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25162O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25162O\"></sup>Matthew and Thomas; James <i>the son</i> of Alphaeus, and Simon who was called the Zealot;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Judas <i>the son</i> of James, and Judas Iscariot, who became a traitor.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Jesus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25164P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25164P\"></sup>came down with them and stood on a level place; and <i>there was</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25164Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25164Q\"></sup>a large crowd of His disciples, and a great throng of people from all Judea and Jerusalem and the coastal region of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25164R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25164R\"></sup>Tyre and Sidon,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>who had come to hear Him and to be healed of their diseases; and those who were troubled with unclean spirits were being cured.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And all the people were trying to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25166S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25166S\"></sup>touch Him, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25166T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25166T\"></sup>power was coming from Him and healing <i>them</i> all.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And turning His gaze toward His disciples, He <i>began</i> to say, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25167U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25167U\"></sup>Blessed <i>are</i> you <i>who are</i> poor, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25167V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25167V\"></sup>yours is the kingdom of God.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Blessed <i>are</i> you who hunger now, for you shall be satisfied. Blessed <i>are</i> you who weep now, for you shall laugh.</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25169W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25169W\"></sup>Blessed are you when men hate you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25169X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25169X\"></sup>ostracize you, and insult you, and scorn your name as evil, for the sake of the Son of Man.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Be glad in that day and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25170Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25170Y\"></sup>leap <i>for joy</i>, for behold, your reward is great in heaven. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25170Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25170Z\"></sup>in the same way their fathers used to treat the prophets.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But woe to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25171AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25171AA\"></sup>you who are rich, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25171AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25171AB\"></sup>you are receiving your comfort in full.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Woe to you who are well-fed now, for you shall be hungry. Woe <i>to you</i> who laugh now, for you shall mourn and weep.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Woe <i>to you</i> when all men speak well of you, for their fathers used to treat the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25173AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25173AC\"></sup>false prophets in the same way.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“But I say to you who hear, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25174AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25174AD\"></sup>love your enemies, do good to those who hate you,</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>bless those who curse you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25175AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25175AE\"></sup>pray for those who mistreat you.</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25176AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25176AF\"></sup>Whoever hits you on the cheek, offer him the other also; and whoever takes away your coat, do not withhold your shirt from him either.</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Give to everyone who asks of you, and whoever takes away what is yours, do not demand it back.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25178AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25178AG\"></sup>Treat others the same way you want them to treat you.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25179AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25179AH\"></sup>If you love those who love you, what credit is <i>that</i> to you? For even sinners love those who love them.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>If you do good to those who do good to you, what credit is <i>that</i> to you? For even sinners do the same.</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25181AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25181AI\"></sup>If you lend to those from whom you expect to receive, what credit is <i>that</i> to you? Even sinners lend to sinners in order to receive back the same <i>amount</i>.</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25182AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25182AJ\"></sup>love your enemies, and do good, and lend, expecting nothing in return; and your reward will be great, and you will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25182AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25182AK\"></sup>sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25182AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25182AL\"></sup>the Most High; for He Himself is kind to ungrateful and evil <i>men</i>.</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Be merciful, just as your Father is merciful.</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25184AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25184AM\"></sup>Do not judge, and you will not be judged; and do not condemn, and you will not be condemned; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25184AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25184AN\"></sup>pardon, and you will be pardoned.</span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Give, and it will be given to you. They will pour <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25185AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25185AO\"></sup>into your lap a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25185AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25185AP\"></sup>good measure—pressed down, shaken together, <i>and</i> running over. For by your standard of measure it will be measured to you in return.”</span>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And He also spoke a parable to them: <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25186AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25186AQ\"></sup>A blind man cannot guide a blind man, can he? Will they not both fall into a pit?</span>",
			"40": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25187AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25187AR\"></sup>A pupil is not above his teacher; but everyone, after he has been fully trained, will be like his teacher.</span>",
			"41": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Why do you look at the speck that is in your brother’s eye, but do not notice the log that is in your own eye?</span>",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Or how can you say to your brother, ‘Brother, let me take out the speck that is in your eye,’ when you yourself do not see the log that is in your own eye? You hypocrite, first take the log out of your own eye, and then you will see clearly to take out the speck that is in your brother’s eye.</span>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25190AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25190AS\"></sup>For there is no good tree which produces bad fruit, nor, on the other hand, a bad tree which produces good fruit.</span>",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25191AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25191AT\"></sup>For each tree is known by its own fruit. For men do not gather figs from thorns, nor do they pick grapes from a briar bush.</span>",
			"45": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25192AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25192AU\"></sup>The good man out of the good treasure of his heart brings forth what is good; and the evil <i>man</i> out of the evil <i>treasure</i> brings forth what is evil; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25192AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25192AV\"></sup>for his mouth speaks from that which fills his heart.</span>",
			"46": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25193AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25193AW\"></sup>Why do you call Me, ‘Lord, Lord,’ and do not do what I say?</span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25194AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25194AX\"></sup>Everyone who comes to Me and hears My words and acts on them, I will show you whom he is like:</span>",
			"48": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>he is like a man building a house, who dug deep and laid a foundation on the rock; and when a flood occurred, the torrent burst against that house and could not shake it, because it had been well built.</span>",
			"49": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>But the one who has heard and has not acted <i>accordingly</i>, is like a man who built a house on the ground without any foundation; and the torrent burst against it and immediately it collapsed, and the ruin of that house was great.”</span>"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25197A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25197A\"></sup>When He had completed all His discourse in the hearing of the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25197B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25197B\"></sup>He went to Capernaum.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And a centurion’s slave, who was highly regarded by him, was sick and about to die.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When he heard about Jesus, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25199C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25199C\"></sup>he sent some Jewish elders asking Him to come and save the life of his slave.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When they came to Jesus, they earnestly implored Him, saying, “He is worthy for You to grant this to him;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>for he loves our nation and it was he who built us our synagogue.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now Jesus <i>started</i> on His way with them; and when He was not far from the house, the centurion sent friends, saying to Him, “Lord, do not trouble Yourself further, for I am not worthy for You to come under my roof;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>for this reason I did not even consider myself worthy to come to You, but <i>just</i> say the word, and my servant will be healed.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For I also am a man placed under authority, with soldiers under me; and I say to this one, ‘Go!’ and he goes, and to another, ‘Come!’ and he comes, and to my slave, ‘Do this!’ and he does it.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now when Jesus heard this, He marveled at him, and turned and said to the crowd that was following Him, <span class=\"woj\">“I say to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25205D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25205D\"></sup>not even in Israel have I found such great faith.”</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When those who had been sent returned to the house, they found the slave in good health.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Soon afterwards He went to a city called Nain; and His disciples were going along with Him, accompanied by a large crowd.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now as He approached the gate of the city, a dead man was being carried out, the only son of his mother, and she was a widow; and a sizeable crowd from the city was with her.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25209E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25209E\"></sup>the Lord saw her, He felt compassion for her, and said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“Do not weep.”</span>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And He came up and touched the coffin; and the bearers came to a halt. And He said, <span class=\"woj\">“Young man, I say to you, arise!”</span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The dead man sat up and began to speak. And <i>Jesus</i> gave him back to his mother.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25212F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25212F\"></sup>Fear gripped them all, and they <i>began</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25212G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25212G\"></sup>glorifying God, saying, “A great <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25212H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25212H\"></sup>prophet has arisen among us!” and, “God has visited His people!”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25213I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25213I\"></sup>This report concerning Him went out all over Judea and in all the surrounding district.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25214J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25214J\"></sup>The disciples of John reported to him about all these things.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Summoning two of his disciples, John sent them to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25215K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25215K\"></sup>the Lord, saying, “Are You the Expected One, or do we look for someone else?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When the men came to Him, they said, “John the Baptist has sent us to You, to ask, ‘Are You the Expected One, or do we look for someone else?’”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>At that very time He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25217L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25217L\"></sup>cured many <i>people</i> of diseases and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25217M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25217M\"></sup>afflictions and evil spirits; and He gave sight to many <i>who were</i> blind.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And He answered and said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Go and report to John what you have seen and heard: <i>the</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25218N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25218N\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">blind receive sight</span>, <i>the</i> lame walk, <i>the</i> lepers are cleansed, and <i>the</i> deaf hear, <i>the</i> dead are raised up, <i>the</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25218O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25218O\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">poor have the gospel preached to them</span>.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Blessed is he who does not take offense at Me.”</span>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When the messengers of John had left, He began to speak to the crowds about John, <span class=\"woj\">“What did you go out into the wilderness to see? A reed shaken by the wind?</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But what did you go out to see? A man dressed in soft clothing? Those who are splendidly clothed and live in luxury are <i>found</i> in royal palaces!</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But what did you go out to see? A prophet? Yes, I say to you, and one who is more than a prophet.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>This is the one about whom it is written,</span><span class=\"woj\">‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25223P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25223P\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Behold</span>, I <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">send My messenger</span> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">ahead of You</span>,</span><span class=\"woj\"><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Who will prepare Your way before You</span>.’</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>I say to you, among those born of women there is no one greater than John; yet he who is least in the kingdom of God is greater than he.”</span>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When all the people and the tax collectors heard <i>this</i>, they acknowledged <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25225Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25225Q\"></sup>God’s justice, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25225R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25225R\"></sup>having been baptized with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25225S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25225S\"></sup>the baptism of John.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But the Pharisees and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25226T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25226T\"></sup>lawyers rejected God’s purpose for themselves, not having been baptized by John.",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“To what then shall I compare the men of this generation, and what are they like?</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They are like children who sit in the market place and call to one another, and they say, ‘We played the flute for you, and you did not dance; we sang a dirge, and you did not weep.’</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>For John the Baptist has come <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25229U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25229U\"></sup>eating no bread and drinking no wine, and you say, ‘He has a demon!’</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The Son of Man has come eating and drinking, and you say, ‘Behold, a gluttonous man and a drunkard, a friend of tax collectors and sinners!’</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Yet wisdom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25231V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25231V\"></sup>is vindicated by all her children.”</span>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Now one of the Pharisees was requesting Him to dine with him, and He entered the Pharisee’s house and reclined <i>at the table</i>.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25233W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25233W\"></sup>And there was a woman in the city who was a sinner; and when she learned that He was reclining <i>at the table</i> in the Pharisee’s house, she brought an alabaster vial of perfume,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>and standing behind <i>Him</i> at His feet, weeping, she began to wet His feet with her tears, and kept wiping them with the hair of her head, and kissing His feet and anointing them with the perfume.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Now when the Pharisee who had invited Him saw this, he said to himself, “If this man were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25235X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25235X\"></sup>a prophet He would know who and what sort of person this woman is who is touching Him, that she is a sinner.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And Jesus answered him, <span class=\"woj\">“Simon, I have something to say to you.”</span> And he replied, “Say it, Teacher.”",
			"41": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“A moneylender had two debtors: one owed five hundred <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25237Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25237Y\"></sup>denarii, and the other fifty.</span>",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>When they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25238Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25238Z\"></sup>were unable to repay, he graciously forgave them both. So which of them will love him more?”</span>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Simon answered and said, “I suppose the one whom he forgave more.” And He said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“You have judged correctly.”</span>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Turning toward the woman, He said to Simon, <span class=\"woj\">“Do you see this woman? I entered your house; you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25240AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25240AA\"></sup>gave Me no water for My feet, but she has wet My feet with her tears and wiped them with her hair.</span>",
			"45": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25241AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25241AB\"></sup>gave Me no kiss; but she, since the time I came in, has not ceased to kiss My feet.</span>",
			"46": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25242AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25242AC\"></sup>You did not anoint My head with oil, but she anointed My feet with perfume.</span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>For this reason I say to you, her sins, which are many, have been forgiven, for she loved much; but he who is forgiven little, loves little.”</span>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Then He said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25244AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25244AD\"></sup>Your sins have been forgiven.”</span>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Those who were reclining <i>at the table</i> with Him began to say to themselves, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25245AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25245AE\"></sup>Who is this <i>man</i> who even forgives sins?”",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>And He said to the woman, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25246AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25246AF\"></sup>Your faith has saved you; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25246AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25246AG\"></sup>go in peace.”</span>"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Soon afterwards, He <i>began</i> going around from one city and village to another, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25247A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25247A\"></sup>proclaiming and preaching the kingdom of God. The twelve were with Him,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and <i>also</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25248B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25248B\"></sup>some women who had been healed of evil spirits and sicknesses: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25248C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25248C\"></sup>Mary who was called Magdalene, from whom seven demons had gone out,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and Joanna the wife of Chuza, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25249D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25249D\"></sup>Herod’s <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25249E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25249E\"></sup>steward, and Susanna, and many others who were contributing to their support out of their private means.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25250F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25250F\"></sup>When a large crowd was coming together, and those from the various cities were journeying to Him, He spoke by way of a parable:",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“The sower went out to sow his seed; and as he sowed, some fell beside the road, and it was trampled under foot and the birds of the air ate it up.</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Other <i>seed</i> fell on rocky <i>soil</i>, and as soon as it grew up, it withered away, because it had no moisture.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Other <i>seed</i> fell among the thorns; and the thorns grew up with it and choked it out.</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Other <i>seed</i> fell into the good soil, and grew up, and produced a crop a hundred times as great.”</span> As He said these things, He would call out, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25254G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25254G\"></sup>He who has ears to hear, let him hear.”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25255H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25255H\"></sup>His disciples <i>began</i> questioning Him as to what this parable meant.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And He said, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25256I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25256I\"></sup>To you it has been granted to know the mysteries of the kingdom of God, but to the rest <i>it is</i> in parables, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25256J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25256J\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">seeing they may not see, and hearing they may not understand</span>.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Now the parable is this: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25257K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25257K\"></sup>the seed is the word of God.</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Those beside the road are those who have heard; then the devil comes and takes away the word from their heart, so that they will not believe and be saved.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Those on the rocky <i>soil are</i> those who, when they hear, receive the word with joy; and these have no <i>firm</i> root; they believe for a while, and in time of temptation fall away.</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <i>seed</i> which fell among the thorns, these are the ones who have heard, and as they go on their way they are choked with worries and riches and pleasures of <i>this</i> life, and bring no fruit to maturity.</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But the <i>seed</i> in the good soil, these are the ones who have heard the word in an honest and good heart, and hold it fast, and bear fruit with perseverance.</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25262L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25262L\"></sup>no one after lighting a lamp covers it over with a container, or puts it under a bed; but he puts it on a lampstand, so that those who come in may see the light.</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25263M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25263M\"></sup>For nothing is hidden that will not become evident, nor <i>anything</i> secret that will not be known and come to light.</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So take care how you listen; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25264N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25264N\"></sup>for whoever has, to him <i>more</i> shall be given; and whoever does not have, even what he thinks he has shall be taken away from him.”</span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25265O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25265O\"></sup>And His mother and brothers came to Him, and they were unable to get to Him because of the crowd.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And it was reported to Him, “Your mother and Your brothers are standing outside, wishing to see You.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But He answered and said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“My mother and My brothers are these <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25267P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25267P\"></sup>who hear the word of God and do it.”</span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25268Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25268Q\"></sup>Now on one of <i>those</i> days Jesus and His disciples got into a boat, and He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Let us go over to the other side of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25268R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25268R\"></sup>the lake.”</span> So they launched out.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But as they were sailing along He fell asleep; and a fierce gale of wind descended on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25269S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25269S\"></sup>the lake, and they <i>began</i> to be swamped and to be in danger.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>They came to Jesus and woke Him up, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25270T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25270T\"></sup>Master, Master, we are perishing!” And He got up and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25270U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25270U\"></sup>rebuked the wind and the surging waves, and they stopped, and it became calm.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Where is your faith?”</span> They were fearful and amazed, saying to one another, “Who then is this, that He commands even the winds and the water, and they obey Him?”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25272V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25272V\"></sup>Then they sailed to the country of the Gerasenes, which is opposite Galilee.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And when He came out onto the land, He was met by a man from the city who was possessed with demons; and who had not put on any clothing for a long time, and was not living in a house, but in the tombs.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Seeing Jesus, he cried out and fell before Him, and said in a loud voice, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25274W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25274W\"></sup>What business do we have with each other, Jesus, Son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25274X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25274X\"></sup>the Most High God? I beg You, do not torment me.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>For He had commanded the unclean spirit to come out of the man. For it had seized him many times; and he was bound with chains and shackles and kept under guard, and <i>yet</i> he would break his bonds and be driven by the demon into the desert.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And Jesus asked him, <span class=\"woj\">“What is your name?”</span> And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25276Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25276Y\"></sup>Legion”; for many demons had entered him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>They were imploring Him not to command them to go away into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25277Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25277Z\"></sup>the abyss.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Now there was a herd of many swine feeding there on the mountain; and <i>the demons</i> implored Him to permit them to enter the swine. And He gave them permission.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And the demons came out of the man and entered the swine; and the herd rushed down the steep bank into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25279AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25279AA\"></sup>the lake and was drowned.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When the herdsmen saw what had happened, they ran away and reported it in the city and <i>out</i> in the country.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><i>The people</i> went out to see what had happened; and they came to Jesus, and found the man from whom the demons had gone out, sitting down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25281AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25281AB\"></sup>at the feet of Jesus, clothed and in his right mind; and they became frightened.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Those who had seen it reported to them how the man who was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25282AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25282AC\"></sup>demon-possessed had been made well.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And all the people of the country of the Gerasenes and the surrounding district asked Him to leave them, for they were gripped with great fear; and He got into a boat and returned.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25284AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25284AD\"></sup>But the man from whom the demons had gone out was begging Him that he might accompany Him; but He sent him away, saying,",
			"39": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“Return to your house and describe what great things God has done for you.”</span> So he went away, proclaiming throughout the whole city what great things Jesus had done for him.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25286AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25286AE\"></sup>And as Jesus returned, the people welcomed Him, for they had all been waiting for Him.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25287AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25287AF\"></sup>And there came a man named Jairus, and he was an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25287AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25287AG\"></sup>official of the synagogue; and he fell at Jesus’ feet, and <i>began</i> to implore Him to come to his house;",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>for he had an only daughter, about twelve years old, and she was dying. But as He went, the crowds were pressing against Him.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And a woman who had a hemorrhage for twelve years, and could not be healed by anyone,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>came up behind Him and touched the fringe of His cloak, and immediately her hemorrhage stopped.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>And Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Who is the one who touched Me?”</span> And while they were all denying it, Peter said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25291AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25291AH\"></sup>Master, the people are crowding and pressing in on You.”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>But Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Someone did touch Me, for I was aware that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25292AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25292AI\"></sup>power had gone out of Me.”</span>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>When the woman saw that she had not escaped notice, she came trembling and fell down before Him, and declared in the presence of all the people the reason why she had touched Him, and how she had been immediately healed.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>And He said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“Daughter, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25294AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25294AJ\"></sup>your faith has made you well; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25294AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25294AK\"></sup>go in peace.”</span>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>While He was still speaking, someone *came from <i>the house of</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25295AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25295AL\"></sup>the synagogue official, saying, “Your daughter has died; do not trouble the Teacher anymore.”",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>But when Jesus heard <i>this</i>, He answered him, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25296AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25296AM\"></sup>Do not be afraid <i>any longer</i>; only believe, and she will be made well.”</span>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>When He came to the house, He did not allow anyone to enter with Him, except Peter and John and James, and the girl’s father and mother.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Now they were all weeping and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25298AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25298AN\"></sup>lamenting for her; but He said, <span class=\"woj\">“Stop weeping, for she has not died, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25298AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25298AO\"></sup>is asleep.”</span>",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>And they <i>began</i> laughing at Him, knowing that she had died.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>He, however, took her by the hand and called, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“Child, arise!”</span>",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>And her spirit returned, and she got up immediately; and He gave orders for <i>something</i> to be given her to eat.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>Her parents were amazed; but He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25302AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25302AP\"></sup>instructed them to tell no one what had happened."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25303A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25303A\"></sup>And He called the twelve together, and gave them power and authority over all the demons and to heal diseases.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And He sent them out to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25304B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25304B\"></sup>proclaim the kingdom of God and to perform healing.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25305C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25305C\"></sup>Take nothing for <i>your</i> journey, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25305D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25305D\"></sup>neither a staff, nor a bag, nor bread, nor money; and do not <i>even</i> have two tunics apiece.</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Whatever house you enter, stay there until you leave that city.</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And as for those who do not receive you, as you go out from that city, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25307E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25307E\"></sup>shake the dust off your feet as a testimony against them.”</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Departing, they <i>began</i> going throughout the villages, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25308F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25308F\"></sup>preaching the gospel and healing everywhere.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25309G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25309G\"></sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25309H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25309H\"></sup>Herod the tetrarch heard of all that was happening; and he was greatly perplexed, because it was said by some that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25309I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25309I\"></sup>John had risen from the dead,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and by some that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25310J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25310J\"></sup>Elijah had appeared, and by others that one of the prophets of old had risen again.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Herod said, “I myself had John beheaded; but who is this man about whom I hear such things?” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25311K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25311K\"></sup>he kept trying to see Him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25312L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25312L\"></sup>When the apostles returned, they gave an account to Him of all that they had done. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25312M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25312M\"></sup>Taking them with Him, He withdrew by Himself to a city called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25312N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25312N\"></sup>Bethsaida.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But the crowds were aware of this and followed Him; and welcoming them, He <i>began</i> speaking to them about the kingdom of God and curing those who had need of healing.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now the day was ending, and the twelve came and said to Him, “Send the crowd away, that they may go into the surrounding villages and countryside and find lodging and get something to eat; for here we are in a desolate place.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“You give them <i>something</i> to eat!”</span> And they said, “We have no more than five loaves and two fish, unless perhaps we go and buy food for all these people.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>(For there were about five thousand men.) And He said to His disciples, <span class=\"woj\">“Have them sit down <i>to eat</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25316O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25316O\"></sup>in groups of about fifty each.”</span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They did so, and had them all sit down.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then He took the five loaves and the two fish, and looking up to heaven, He blessed them, and broke <i>them</i>, and kept giving <i>them</i> to the disciples to set before the people.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And they all ate and were satisfied; and the broken pieces which they had left over were picked up, twelve <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25319P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25319P\"></sup>baskets <i>full</i>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25320Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25320Q\"></sup>And it happened that while He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25320R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25320R\"></sup>praying alone, the disciples were with Him, and He questioned them, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“Who do the people say that I am?”</span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They answered and said, “John the Baptist, and others <i>say</i> Elijah; but others, that one of the prophets of old has risen again.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“But who do you say that I am?”</span> And Peter answered and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25322S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25322S\"></sup>The Christ of God.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25323T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25323T\"></sup>warned them and instructed <i>them</i> not to tell this to anyone,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25324U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25324U\"></sup>saying, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25324V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25324V\"></sup>The Son of Man must suffer many things and be rejected by the elders and chief priests and scribes, and be killed and be raised up on the third day.”</span>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And He was saying to <i>them</i> all, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25325W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25325W\"></sup>If anyone wishes to come after Me, he must deny himself, and take up his cross daily and follow Me.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25326X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25326X\"></sup>whoever wishes to save his life will lose it, but whoever loses his life for My sake, he is the one who will save it.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For what is a man profited if he gains the whole world, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25327Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25327Y\"></sup>loses or forfeits himself?</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25328Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25328Z\"></sup>For whoever is ashamed of Me and My words, the Son of Man will be ashamed of him when He comes in His glory, and <i>the glory</i> of the Father and of the holy angels.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But I say to you truthfully, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25329AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25329AA\"></sup>there are some of those standing here who will not taste death until they see the kingdom of God.”</span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25330AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25330AB\"></sup>Some eight days after these sayings, He took along <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25330AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25330AC\"></sup>Peter and John and James, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25330AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25330AD\"></sup>went up on the mountain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25330AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25330AE\"></sup>to pray.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And while He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25331AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25331AF\"></sup>praying, the appearance of His face <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25331AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25331AG\"></sup>became different, and His clothing <i>became</i> white <i>and</i> gleaming.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And behold, two men were talking with Him; and they were Moses and Elijah,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>who, appearing in glory, were speaking of His <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25333AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25333AH\"></sup>departure which He was about to accomplish at Jerusalem.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Now Peter and his companions <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25334AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25334AI\"></sup>had been overcome with sleep; but when they were fully awake, they saw His glory and the two men standing with Him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And as these were leaving Him, Peter said to Jesus, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25335AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25335AJ\"></sup>Master, it is good for us to be here; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25335AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25335AK\"></sup>let us make three tabernacles: one for You, and one for Moses, and one for Elijah”—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25335AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25335AL\"></sup>not realizing what he was saying.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>While he was saying this, a cloud formed and <i>began</i> to overshadow them; and they were afraid as they entered the cloud.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25337AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25337AM\"></sup>a voice came out of the cloud, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25337AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25337AN\"></sup>This is My Son, <i>My</i> Chosen One; listen to Him!”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And when the voice had spoken, Jesus was found alone. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25338AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25338AO\"></sup>they kept silent, and reported to no one in those days any of the things which they had seen.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25339AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25339AP\"></sup>On the next day, when they came down from the mountain, a large crowd met Him.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And a man from the crowd shouted, saying, “Teacher, I beg You to look at my son, for he is my only <i>boy</i>,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>and a spirit seizes him, and he suddenly screams, and it throws him into a convulsion with foaming <i>at the mouth</i>; and only with difficulty does it leave him, mauling him <i>as it leaves</i>.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>I begged Your disciples to cast it out, and they could not.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And Jesus answered and said, <span class=\"woj\">“You unbelieving and perverted generation, how long shall I be with you and put up with you? Bring your son here.”</span>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>While he was still approaching, the demon slammed him <i>to the ground</i> and threw him into a convulsion. But Jesus rebuked the unclean spirit, and healed the boy and gave him back to his father.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And they were all amazed at the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25345AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25345AQ\"></sup>greatness of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25345AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25345AR\"></sup>But while everyone was marveling at all that He was doing, He said to His disciples,",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>“Let these words sink into your ears; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25346AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25346AS\"></sup>for the Son of Man is going to be delivered into the hands of men.”</span>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25347AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25347AT\"></sup>they did not understand this statement, and it was concealed from them so that they would not perceive it; and they were afraid to ask Him about this statement.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25348AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25348AU\"></sup>An argument started among them as to which of them might be the greatest.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>But Jesus, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25349AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25349AV\"></sup>knowing what they were thinking in their heart, took a child and stood him by His side,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>and said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25350AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25350AW\"></sup>Whoever receives this child in My name receives Me, and whoever receives Me receives Him who sent Me; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25350AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25350AX\"></sup>for the one who is least among all of you, this is the one who is great.”</span>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25351AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25351AY\"></sup>John answered and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25351AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25351AZ\"></sup>Master, we saw someone casting out demons in Your name; and we tried to prevent him because he does not follow along with us.”",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>But Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Do not hinder <i>him</i>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25352BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25352BA\"></sup>for he who is not against you is for you.”</span>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>When the days were approaching for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25353BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25353BB\"></sup>His ascension, He was determined <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25353BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25353BC\"></sup>to go to Jerusalem;",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>and He sent messengers on ahead of Him, and they went and entered a village of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25354BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25354BD\"></sup>Samaritans to make arrangements for Him.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>But they did not receive Him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25355BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25355BE\"></sup>because He was traveling toward Jerusalem.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>When His disciples <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25356BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25356BF\"></sup>James and John saw <i>this</i>, they said, “Lord, do You want us to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25356BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25356BG\"></sup>command fire to come down from heaven and consume them?”",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>But He turned and rebuked them, [and said, <span class=\"woj\">“You do not know what kind of spirit you are of;</span>",
			"56": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>for the Son of Man did not come to destroy men’s lives, but to save them.”</span>] And they went on to another village.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25359BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25359BH\"></sup>As they were going along the road, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25359BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25359BI\"></sup>someone said to Him, “I will follow You wherever You go.”",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>And Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“The foxes have holes and the birds of the air <i>have</i> nests, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25360BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25360BJ\"></sup>the Son of Man has nowhere to lay His head.”</span>",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>And He said to another, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25361BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25361BK\"></sup>Follow Me.”</span> But he said, “Lord, permit me first to go and bury my father.”",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>But He said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Allow the dead to bury their own dead; but as for you, go and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25362BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25362BL\"></sup>proclaim everywhere the kingdom of God.”</span>",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>Another also said, “I will follow You, Lord; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25363BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25363BM\"></sup>first permit me to say good-bye to those at home.”",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>But Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25364BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25364BN\"></sup>No one, after putting his hand to the plow and looking back, is fit for the kingdom of God.”</span>"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Now after this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25365A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25365A\"></sup>the Lord appointed seventy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25365B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25365B\"></sup>others, and sent them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25365C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25365C\"></sup>in pairs ahead of Him to every city and place where He Himself was going to come.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And He was saying to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25366D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25366D\"></sup>The harvest is plentiful, but the laborers are few; therefore beseech the Lord of the harvest to send out laborers into His harvest.</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Go; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25367E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25367E\"></sup>behold, I send you out as lambs in the midst of wolves.</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25368F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25368F\"></sup>Carry no money belt, no bag, no shoes; and greet no one on the way.</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Whatever house you enter, first say, ‘Peace <i>be</i> to this house.’</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>If a man of peace is there, your peace will rest on him; but if not, it will return to you.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Stay in that house, eating and drinking what they give you; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25371G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25371G\"></sup>the laborer is worthy of his wages. Do not keep moving from house to house.</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Whatever city you enter and they receive you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25372H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25372H\"></sup>eat what is set before you;</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and heal those in it who are sick, and say to them, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25373I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25373I\"></sup>The kingdom of God has come near to you.’</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But whatever city you enter and they do not receive you, go out into its streets and say,</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25375J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25375J\"></sup>Even the dust of your city which clings to our feet we wipe off <i>in protest</i> against you; yet be sure of this, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25375K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25375K\"></sup>the kingdom of God has come near.’</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I say to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25376L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25376L\"></sup>it will be more tolerable in that day for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25376M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25376M\"></sup>Sodom than for that city.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25377N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25377N\"></sup>Woe to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25377O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25377O\"></sup>Chorazin! Woe to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25377P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25377P\"></sup>Bethsaida! For if the miracles had been performed in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25377Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25377Q\"></sup>Tyre and Sidon which occurred in you, they would have repented long ago, sitting in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25377R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25377R\"></sup>sackcloth and ashes.</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But it will be more tolerable for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25378S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25378S\"></sup>Tyre and Sidon in the judgment than for you.</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25379T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25379T\"></sup>Capernaum, will not be exalted to heaven, will you? You will be brought down to Hades!</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25380U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25380U\"></sup>The one who listens to you listens to Me, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25380V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25380V\"></sup>the one who rejects you rejects Me; and he who rejects Me rejects the One who sent Me.”</span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The seventy returned with joy, saying, “Lord, even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25381W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25381W\"></sup>the demons are subject to us in Your name.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“I was watching <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25382X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25382X\"></sup>Satan fall from heaven like lightning.</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Behold, I have given you authority to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25383Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25383Y\"></sup>tread on serpents and scorpions, and over all the power of the enemy, and nothing will injure you.</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Nevertheless do not rejoice in this, that the spirits are subject to you, but rejoice that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25384Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25384Z\"></sup>your names are recorded in heaven.”</span>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25385AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25385AA\"></sup>At that very time He rejoiced greatly in the Holy Spirit, and said, <span class=\"woj\">“I praise You, O Father, Lord of heaven and earth, that You have hidden these things from <i>the</i> wise and intelligent and have revealed them to infants. Yes, Father, for this way was well-pleasing in Your sight.</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25386AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25386AB\"></sup>All things have been handed over to Me by My Father, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25386AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25386AC\"></sup>no one knows who the Son is except the Father, and who the Father is except the Son, and anyone to whom the Son wills to reveal <i>Him</i>.”</span>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25387AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25387AD\"></sup>Turning to the disciples, He said privately, <span class=\"woj\">“Blessed <i>are</i> the eyes which see the things you see,</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>for I say to you, that many prophets and kings wished to see the things which you see, and did not see <i>them</i>, and to hear the things which you hear, and did not hear <i>them</i>.”</span>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25389AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25389AE\"></sup>And a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25389AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25389AF\"></sup>lawyer stood up and put Him to the test, saying, “Teacher, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And He said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“What is written in the Law? How does it read to you?”</span>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And he answered, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25391AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25391AG\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, and with all your soul, and with all your strength, and with all your mind; and your neighbor as yourself</span>.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And He said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“You have answered correctly; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25392AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25392AH\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">do this and you will live</span>.”</span>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But wishing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25393AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25393AI\"></sup>to justify himself, he said to Jesus, “And who is my neighbor?”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Jesus replied and said, <span class=\"woj\">“A man was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25394AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25394AJ\"></sup>going down from Jerusalem to Jericho, and fell among robbers, and they stripped him and beat him, and went away leaving him half dead.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And by chance a priest was going down on that road, and when he saw him, he passed by on the other side.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Likewise a Levite also, when he came to the place and saw him, passed by on the other side.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25397AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25397AK\"></sup>Samaritan, who was on a journey, came upon him; and when he saw him, he felt compassion,</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>and came to him and bandaged up his wounds, pouring oil and wine on <i>them</i>; and he put him on his own beast, and brought him to an inn and took care of him.</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>On the next day he took out two denarii and gave them to the innkeeper and said, ‘Take care of him; and whatever more you spend, when I return I will repay you.’</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Which of these three do you think proved to be a neighbor to the man who fell into the robbers’ <i>hands</i>?”</span>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And he said, “The one who showed mercy toward him.” Then Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Go and do the same.”</span>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Now as they were traveling along, He entered a village; and a woman named <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25402AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25402AL\"></sup>Martha welcomed Him into her home.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>She had a sister called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25403AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25403AM\"></sup>Mary, who was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25403AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25403AN\"></sup>seated at the Lord’s feet, listening to His word.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25404AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25404AO\"></sup>Martha was distracted with all her preparations; and she came up <i>to Him</i> and said, “Lord, do You not care that my sister has left me to do all the serving alone? Then tell her to help me.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>But the Lord answered and said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25405AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25405AP\"></sup>Martha, Martha, you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25405AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25405AQ\"></sup>worried and bothered about so many things;</span>",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25406AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25406AR\"></sup>but <i>only</i> one thing is necessary, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25406AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25406AS\"></sup>Mary has chosen the good part, which shall not be taken away from her.”</span>"
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>It happened that while Jesus was praying in a certain place, after He had finished, one of His disciples said to Him, “Lord, teach us to pray just as John also taught his disciples.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25408A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25408A\"></sup>When you pray, say:</span><span class=\"woj\">‘Father, hallowed be Your name.</span><span class=\"woj\">Your kingdom come.</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>‘Give us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25409B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25409B\"></sup>each day our daily bread.</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>‘And forgive us our sins,</span><span class=\"woj\">For we ourselves also forgive everyone who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25410C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25410C\"></sup>is indebted to us.</span><span class=\"woj\">And lead us not into temptation.’”</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Suppose one of you has a friend, and goes to him at midnight and says to him, ‘Friend, lend me three loaves;</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>for a friend of mine has come to me from a journey, and I have nothing to set before him’;</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and from inside he answers and says, ‘Do not bother me; the door has already been shut and my children and I are in bed; I cannot get up and give you <i>anything</i>.’</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I tell you, even though he will not get up and give him <i>anything</i> because he is his friend, yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25414D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25414D\"></sup>because of his persistence he will get up and give him as much as he needs.</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“So I say to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25415E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25415E\"></sup>ask, and it will be given to you; seek, and you will find; knock, and it will be opened to you.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For everyone who asks, receives; and he who seeks, finds; and to him who knocks, it will be opened.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now suppose one of you fathers is asked by his son for a fish; he will not give him a snake instead of a fish, will he?</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Or <i>if</i> he is asked for an egg, he will not give him a scorpion, will he?</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25419F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25419F\"></sup>If you then, being evil, know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will <i>your</i> heavenly Father give the Holy Spirit to those who ask Him?”</span>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25420G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25420G\"></sup>And He was casting out a demon, and it was mute; when the demon had gone out, the mute man spoke; and the crowds were amazed.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But some of them said, “He casts out demons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25421H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25421H\"></sup>by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25421I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25421I\"></sup>Beelzebul, the ruler of the demons.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Others, to test <i>Him</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25422J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25422J\"></sup>were demanding of Him a sign from heaven.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25423K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25423K\"></sup>But He knew their thoughts and said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Any kingdom divided against itself is laid waste; and a house <i>divided</i> against itself falls.</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>If <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25424L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25424L\"></sup>Satan also is divided against himself, how will his kingdom stand? For you say that I cast out demons by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25424M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25424M\"></sup>Beelzebul.</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And if I by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25425N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25425N\"></sup>Beelzebul cast out demons, by whom do your sons cast them out? So they will be your judges.</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But if I cast out demons by the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25426O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25426O\"></sup>finger of God, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25426P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25426P\"></sup>the kingdom of God has come upon you.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When a strong <i>man</i>, fully armed, guards his own house, his possessions are undisturbed.</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But when someone stronger than he attacks him and overpowers him, he takes away from him all his armor on which he had relied and distributes his plunder.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25429Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25429Q\"></sup>He who is not with Me is against Me; and he who does not gather with Me, scatters.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25430R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25430R\"></sup>When the unclean spirit goes out of a man, it passes through waterless places seeking rest, and not finding any, it says, ‘I will return to my house from which I came.’</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And when it comes, it finds it swept and put in order.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then it goes and takes <i>along</i> seven other spirits more evil than itself, and they go in and live there; and the last state of that man becomes worse than the first.”</span>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>While Jesus was saying these things, one of the women in the crowd raised her voice and said to Him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25433S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25433S\"></sup>Blessed is the womb that bore You and the breasts at which You nursed.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But He said, <span class=\"woj\">“On the contrary, blessed are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25434T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25434T\"></sup>those who hear the word of God and observe it.”</span>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>As the crowds were increasing, He began to say, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25435U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25435U\"></sup>This generation is a wicked generation; it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25435V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25435V\"></sup>seeks for a sign, and <i>yet</i> no sign will be given to it but the sign of Jonah.</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>For just as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25436W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25436W\"></sup>Jonah became a sign to the Ninevites, so will the Son of Man be to this generation.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25437X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25437X\"></sup>Queen of the South will rise up with the men of this generation at the judgment and condemn them, because she came from the ends of the earth to hear the wisdom of Solomon; and behold, something greater than Solomon is here.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The men of Nineveh will stand up with this generation at the judgment and condemn it, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25438Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25438Y\"></sup>they repented at the preaching of Jonah; and behold, something greater than Jonah is here.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25439Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25439Z\"></sup>No one, after lighting a lamp, puts it away in a cellar nor under a basket, but on the lampstand, so that those who enter may see the light.</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25440AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25440AA\"></sup>The eye is the lamp of your body; when your eye is clear, your whole body also is full of light; but when it is bad, your body also is full of darkness.</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then watch out that the light in you is not darkness.</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>If therefore your whole body is full of light, with no dark part in it, it will be wholly illumined, as when the lamp illumines you with its rays.”</span>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Now when He had spoken, a Pharisee *asked Him to have lunch with him; and He went in, and reclined <i>at the table</i>.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>When the Pharisee saw it, he was surprised that He had not first <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25444AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25444AB\"></sup>ceremonially washed before the meal.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25445AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25445AC\"></sup>the Lord said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25445AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25445AD\"></sup>you Pharisees clean the outside of the cup and of the platter; but inside of you, you are full of robbery and wickedness.</span>",
			"40": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25446AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25446AE\"></sup>You foolish ones, did not He who made the outside make the inside also?</span>",
			"41": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25447AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25447AF\"></sup>give that which is within as charity, and then all things are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25447AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25447AG\"></sup>clean for you.</span>",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25448AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25448AH\"></sup>But woe to you Pharisees! For you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25448AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25448AI\"></sup>pay tithe of mint and rue and every <i>kind of</i> garden herb, and <i>yet</i> disregard justice and the love of God; but these are the things you should have done without neglecting the others.</span>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Woe to you Pharisees! For you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25449AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25449AJ\"></sup>love the chief seats in the synagogues and the respectful greetings in the market places.</span>",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25450AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25450AK\"></sup>Woe to you! For you are like concealed tombs, and the people who walk over <i>them</i> are unaware <i>of it</i>.”</span>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>One of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25451AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25451AL\"></sup>lawyers *said to Him in reply, “Teacher, when You say this, You insult us too.”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>But He said, <span class=\"woj\">“Woe to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25452AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25452AM\"></sup>lawyers as well! For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25452AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25452AN\"></sup>you weigh men down with burdens hard to bear, while you yourselves will not even touch the burdens with one of your fingers.</span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25453AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25453AO\"></sup>Woe to you! For you build the tombs of the prophets, and <i>it was</i> your fathers <i>who</i> killed them.</span>",
			"48": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>So you are witnesses and approve the deeds of your fathers; because it was they who killed them, and you build <i>their tombs</i>.</span>",
			"49": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>For this reason also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25455AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25455AP\"></sup>the wisdom of God said, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25455AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25455AQ\"></sup>I will send to them prophets and apostles, and <i>some</i> of them they will kill and <i>some</i> they will persecute,</span>",
			"50": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>so that the blood of all the prophets, shed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25456AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25456AR\"></sup>since the foundation of the world, may be charged against this generation,</span>",
			"51": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25457AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25457AS\"></sup>the blood of Abel to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25457AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25457AT\"></sup>the blood of Zechariah, who was killed between the altar and the house <i>of God</i>; yes, I tell you, it shall be charged against this generation.’</span>",
			"52": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Woe to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25458AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25458AU\"></sup>lawyers! For you have taken away the key of knowledge; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25458AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25458AV\"></sup>you yourselves did not enter, and you hindered those who were entering.”</span>",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>When He left there, the scribes and the Pharisees began to be very hostile and to question Him closely on many subjects,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25460AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25460AW\"></sup>plotting against Him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25460AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25460AX\"></sup>to catch <i>Him</i> in something He might say."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Under these circumstances, after so many thousands of people had gathered together that they were stepping on one another, He began saying to His disciples first <i>of all</i>, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25461A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25461A\"></sup>Beware of the leaven of the Pharisees, which is hypocrisy.</span>",
			"2": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25462B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25462B\"></sup>But there is nothing covered up that will not be revealed, and hidden that will not be known.</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Accordingly, whatever you have said in the dark will be heard in the light, and what you have whispered in the inner rooms will be proclaimed upon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25463C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25463C\"></sup>the housetops.</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“I say to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25464D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25464D\"></sup>My friends, do not be afraid of those who kill the body and after that have no more that they can do.</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But I will warn you whom to fear: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25465E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25465E\"></sup>fear the One who, after He has killed, has authority to cast into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25465F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25465F\"></sup>hell; yes, I tell you, fear Him!</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Are not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25466G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25466G\"></sup>five sparrows sold for two cents? <i>Yet</i> not one of them is forgotten before God.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25467H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25467H\"></sup>Indeed, the very hairs of your head are all numbered. Do not fear; you are more valuable than many sparrows.</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“And I say to you, everyone who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25468I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25468I\"></sup>confesses Me before men, the Son of Man will confess him also before the angels of God;</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25469J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25469J\"></sup>he who denies Me before men will be denied <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25469K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25469K\"></sup>before the angels of God.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25470L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25470L\"></sup>And everyone who speaks a word against the Son of Man, it will be forgiven him; but he who blasphemes against the Holy Spirit, it will not be forgiven him.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When they bring you before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25471M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25471M\"></sup>the synagogues and the rulers and the authorities, do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25471N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25471N\"></sup>worry about how or what you are to speak in your defense, or what you are to say;</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25472O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25472O\"></sup>the Holy Spirit will teach you in that very hour what you ought to say.”</span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Someone in the crowd said to Him, “Teacher, tell my brother to divide the <i>family</i> inheritance with me.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But He said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25474P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25474P\"></sup>Man, who appointed Me a judge or arbitrator over you?”</span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25475Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25475Q\"></sup>Beware, and be on your guard against every form of greed; for not <i>even</i> when one has an abundance does his life consist of his possessions.”</span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And He told them a parable, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“The land of a rich man was very productive.</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he began reasoning to himself, saying, ‘What shall I do, since I have no place to store my crops?’</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then he said, ‘This is what I will do: I will tear down my barns and build larger ones, and there I will store all my grain and my goods.</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And I will say to my soul, “Soul, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25479R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25479R\"></sup>you have many goods laid up for many years <i>to come</i>; take your ease, eat, drink <i>and</i> be merry.”’</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But God said to him, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25480S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25480S\"></sup>You fool! This <i>very</i> night <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25480T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25480T\"></sup>your soul is required of you; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25480U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25480U\"></sup><i>now</i> who will own what you have prepared?’</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So is the man who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25481V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25481V\"></sup>stores up treasure for himself, and is not rich toward God.”</span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And He said to His disciples, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25482W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25482W\"></sup>For this reason I say to you, do not worry about <i>your</i> life, <i>as to</i> what you will eat; nor for your body, <i>as to</i> what you will put on.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For life is more than food, and the body more than clothing.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Consider the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25484X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25484X\"></sup>ravens, for they neither sow nor reap; they have no storeroom nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25484Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25484Y\"></sup>barn, and <i>yet</i> God feeds them; how much more valuable you are than the birds!</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And which of you by worrying can add a <i>single</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25485Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25485Z\"></sup>hour to his life’s span?</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>If then you cannot do even a very little thing, why do you worry about other matters?</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Consider the lilies, how they grow: they neither toil nor spin; but I tell you, not even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25487AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25487AA\"></sup>Solomon in all his glory clothed himself like one of these.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But if God so clothes the grass in the field, which is <i>alive</i> today and tomorrow is thrown into the furnace, how much more <i>will He clothe</i> you? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25488AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25488AB\"></sup>You men of little faith!</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And do not seek what you will eat and what you will drink, and do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25489AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25489AC\"></sup>keep worrying.</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>For all these things the nations of the world eagerly seek; but your Father knows that you need these things.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But seek His kingdom, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25491AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25491AD\"></sup>these things will be added to you.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25492AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25492AE\"></sup>Do not be afraid, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25492AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25492AF\"></sup>little flock, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25492AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25492AG\"></sup>your Father has chosen gladly to give you the kingdom.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25493AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25493AH\"></sup>Sell your possessions and give to charity; make yourselves money belts which do not wear out, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25493AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25493AI\"></sup>an unfailing treasure in heaven, where no thief comes near nor moth destroys.</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25494AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25494AJ\"></sup>where your treasure is, there your heart will be also.</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25495AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25495AK\"></sup>Be dressed in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25495AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25495AL\"></sup>readiness, and <i>keep</i> your lamps lit.</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Be like men who are waiting for their master when he returns from the wedding feast, so that they may immediately open <i>the door</i> to him when he comes and knocks.</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Blessed are those slaves whom the master will find <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25497AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25497AM\"></sup>on the alert when he comes; truly I say to you, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25497AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25497AN\"></sup>he will gird himself <i>to serve</i>, and have them recline <i>at the table</i>, and will come up and wait on them.</span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25498AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25498AO\"></sup>Whether he comes in the second watch, or even in the third, and finds <i>them</i> so, blessed are those <i>slaves</i>.</span>",
			"39": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25499AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25499AP\"></sup>But be sure of this, that if the head of the house had known at what hour the thief was coming, he would not have allowed his house to be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25499AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25499AQ\"></sup>broken into.</span>",
			"40": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25500AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25500AR\"></sup>You too, be ready; for the Son of Man is coming at an hour that you do not expect.”</span>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Peter said, “Lord, are You addressing this parable to us, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25501AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25501AS\"></sup>to everyone <i>else</i> as well?”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25502AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25502AT\"></sup>the Lord said, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25502AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25502AU\"></sup>Who then is the faithful and sensible <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25502AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25502AV\"></sup>steward, whom his master will put in charge of his servants, to give them their rations at the proper time?</span>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Blessed is that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25503AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25503AW\"></sup>slave whom his master finds so doing when he comes.</span>",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Truly I say to you that he will put him in charge of all his possessions.</span>",
			"45": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>But if that slave says in his heart, ‘My master will be a long time in coming,’ and begins to beat the slaves, <i>both</i> men and women, and to eat and drink and get drunk;</span>",
			"46": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>the master of that slave will come on a day when he does not expect <i>him</i> and at an hour he does not know, and will cut him in pieces, and assign him a place with the unbelievers.</span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>And that slave who knew his master’s will and did not get ready or act in accord with his will, will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25507AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25507AX\"></sup>receive many lashes,</span>",
			"48": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>but the one who did not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25508AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25508AY\"></sup>know <i>it</i>, and committed deeds worthy of a flogging, will receive but few. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25508AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25508AZ\"></sup>From everyone who has been given much, much will be required; and to whom they entrusted much, of him they will ask all the more.</span>",
			"49": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>“I have come to cast fire upon the earth; and how I wish it were already kindled!</span>",
			"50": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>But I have a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25510BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25510BA\"></sup>baptism to undergo, and how distressed I am until it is accomplished!</span>",
			"51": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25511BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25511BB\"></sup>Do you suppose that I came to grant peace on earth? I tell you, no, but rather division;</span>",
			"52": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>for from now on five <i>members</i> in one household will be divided, three against two and two against three.</span>",
			"53": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>They will be divided, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25513BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25513BC\"></sup>father against son and son against father, mother against daughter and daughter against mother, mother-in-law against daughter-in-law and daughter-in-law against mother-in-law.”</span>",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>And He was also saying to the crowds, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25514BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25514BD\"></sup>When you see a cloud rising in the west, immediately you say, ‘A shower is coming,’ and so it turns out.</span>",
			"55": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>And when <i>you see</i> a south wind blowing, you say, ‘It will be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25515BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25515BE\"></sup>hot day,’ and it turns out <i>that way</i>.</span>",
			"56": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>You hypocrites! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25516BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25516BF\"></sup>You know how to analyze the appearance of the earth and the sky, but why do you not analyze this present time?</span>",
			"57": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>“And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25517BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25517BG\"></sup>why do you not even on your own initiative judge what is right?</span>",
			"58": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25518BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25518BH\"></sup>while you are going with your opponent to appear before the magistrate, on <i>your</i> way <i>there</i> make an effort to settle with him, so that he may not drag you before the judge, and the judge turn you over to the officer, and the officer throw you into prison.</span>",
			"59": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>I say to you, you will not get out of there until you have paid the very last <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25519BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25519BI\"></sup>cent.”</span>"
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>Now on the same occasion there were some present who reported to Him about the Galileans whose blood <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25520A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25520A\"></sup>Pilate had mixed with their sacrifices.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25521B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25521B\"></sup>Do you suppose that these Galileans were <i>greater</i> sinners than all <i>other</i> Galileans because they suffered this <i>fate</i>?</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I tell you, no, but unless you repent, you will all likewise perish.</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Or do you suppose that those eighteen on whom the tower in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25523C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25523C\"></sup>Siloam fell and killed them were <i>worse</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25523D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25523D\"></sup>culprits than all the men who live in Jerusalem?</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I tell you, no, but unless you repent, you will all likewise perish.”</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And He <i>began</i> telling this parable: <span class=\"woj\">“A man had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25525E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25525E\"></sup>a fig tree which had been planted in his vineyard; and he came looking for fruit on it and did not find any.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And he said to the vineyard-keeper, ‘Behold, for three years I have come looking for fruit on this fig tree without finding any. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25526F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25526F\"></sup>Cut it down! Why does it even use up the ground?’</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he answered and said to him, ‘Let it alone, sir, for this year too, until I dig around it and put in fertilizer;</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and if it bears fruit next year, <i>fine</i>; but if not, cut it down.’”</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25529G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25529G\"></sup>teaching in one of the synagogues on the Sabbath.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And there was a woman who for eighteen years had had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25530H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25530H\"></sup>a sickness caused by a spirit; and she was bent double, and could not straighten up at all.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Jesus saw her, He called her over and said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“Woman, you are freed from your sickness.”</span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25532I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25532I\"></sup>laid His hands on her; and immediately she was made erect again and <i>began</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25532J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25532J\"></sup>glorifying God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25533K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25533K\"></sup>the synagogue official, indignant because Jesus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25533L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25533L\"></sup>had healed on the Sabbath, <i>began</i> saying to the crowd in response, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25533M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25533M\"></sup>There are six days in which work should be done; so come during them and get healed, and not on the Sabbath day.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25534N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25534N\"></sup>the Lord answered him and said, <span class=\"woj\">“You hypocrites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25534O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25534O\"></sup>does not each of you on the Sabbath untie his ox or his donkey from the stall and lead him away to water <i>him</i>?</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And this woman, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25535P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25535P\"></sup>a daughter of Abraham as she is, whom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25535Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25535Q\"></sup>Satan has bound for eighteen long years, should she not have been released from this bond on the Sabbath day?”</span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>As He said this, all His opponents were being humiliated; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25536R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25536R\"></sup>the entire crowd was rejoicing over all the glorious things being done by Him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25537S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25537S\"></sup>He was saying, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25537T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25537T\"></sup>What is the kingdom of God like, and to what shall I compare it?</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>It is like a mustard seed, which a man took and threw into his own garden; and it grew and became a tree, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25538U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25538U\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">the birds of the</span> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">air nested in its branches</span>.”</span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And again He said, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25539V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25539V\"></sup>To what shall I compare the kingdom of God?</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25540W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25540W\"></sup>It is like leaven, which a woman took and hid in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25540X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25540X\"></sup>three pecks of flour until it was all leavened.”</span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And He was passing through from one city and village to another, teaching, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25541Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25541Y\"></sup>proceeding on His way to Jerusalem.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And someone said to Him, “Lord, are there <i>just</i> a few who are being saved?” And He said to them,",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25543Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25543Z\"></sup>Strive to enter through the narrow door; for many, I tell you, will seek to enter and will not be able.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Once the head of the house gets up and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25544AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25544AA\"></sup>shuts the door, and you begin to stand outside and knock on the door, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25544AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25544AB\"></sup>Lord, open up to us!’ then He will answer and say to you, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25544AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25544AC\"></sup>I do not know where you are from.’</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25545AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25545AD\"></sup>begin to say, ‘We ate and drank in Your presence, and You taught in our streets’;</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and He will say, ‘I tell you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25546AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25546AE\"></sup>I do not know where you are from; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25546AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25546AF\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">depart from Me, all you evildoers</span>.’</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25547AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25547AG\"></sup>In that place there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth when you see Abraham and Isaac and Jacob and all the prophets in the kingdom of God, but yourselves being thrown out.</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25548AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25548AH\"></sup>will come from east and west and from north and south, and will recline <i>at the table</i> in the kingdom of God.</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25549AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25549AI\"></sup><i>some</i> are last who will be first and <i>some</i> are first who will be last.”</span>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Just at that time some Pharisees approached, saying to Him, “Go away, leave here, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25550AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25550AJ\"></sup>Herod wants to kill You.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Go and tell that fox, ‘Behold, I cast out demons and perform cures today and tomorrow, and the third <i>day</i> I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25551AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25551AK\"></sup>reach My goal.’</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Nevertheless <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25552AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25552AL\"></sup>I must journey on today and tomorrow and the next <i>day</i>; for it cannot be that a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25552AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25552AM\"></sup>prophet would perish outside of Jerusalem.</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25553AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25553AN\"></sup>O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, <i>the city</i> that kills the prophets and stones those sent to her! How often I wanted to gather your children together, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25553AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25553AO\"></sup>just as a hen <i>gathers</i> her brood under her wings, and you would not <i>have it</i>!</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Behold, your house is left to you <i>desolate</i>; and I say to you, you will not see Me until <i>the time</i> comes when you say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25554AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25554AP\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Blessed is He who comes in the name of the Lord</span>!’”</span>"
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>It happened that when He went into the house of one of the leaders of the Pharisees on <i>the</i> Sabbath to eat bread, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25555A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25555A\"></sup>they were watching Him closely.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And there in front of Him was a man suffering from dropsy.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Jesus answered and spoke to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25557B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25557B\"></sup>lawyers and Pharisees, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25557C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25557C\"></sup>Is it lawful to heal on the Sabbath, or not?”</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But they kept silent. And He took hold of him and healed him, and sent him away.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25559D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25559D\"></sup>Which one of you will have a son or an ox fall into a well, and will not immediately pull him out on a Sabbath day?”</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25560E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25560E\"></sup>And they could make no reply to this.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And He <i>began</i> speaking a parable to the invited guests when He noticed how <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25561F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25561F\"></sup>they had been picking out the places of honor <i>at the table</i>, saying to them,",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“When you are invited by someone to a wedding feast, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25562G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25562G\"></sup>do not take the place of honor, for someone more distinguished than you may have been invited by him,</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and he who invited you both will come and say to you, ‘Give <i>your</i> place to this man,’ and then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25563H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25563H\"></sup>in disgrace you proceed to occupy the last place.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But when you are invited, go and recline at the last place, so that when the one who has invited you comes, he may say to you, ‘Friend, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25564I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25564I\"></sup>move up higher’; then you will have honor in the sight of all who are at the table with you.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25565J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25565J\"></sup>For everyone who exalts himself will be humbled, and he who humbles himself will be exalted.”</span>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And He also went on to say to the one who had invited Him, <span class=\"woj\">“When you give a luncheon or a dinner, do not invite your friends or your brothers or your relatives or rich neighbors, otherwise they may also invite you in return and <i>that</i> will be your repayment.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But when you give a reception, invite <i>the</i> poor, <i>the</i> crippled, <i>the</i> lame, <i>the</i> blind,</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and you will be blessed, since they do not have <i>the means</i> to repay you; for you will be repaid at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25568K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25568K\"></sup>the resurrection of the righteous.”</span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When one of those who were reclining <i>at the table</i> with Him heard this, he said to Him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25569L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25569L\"></sup>Blessed is everyone who will eat bread in the kingdom of God!”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But He said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25570M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25570M\"></sup>A man was giving a big dinner, and he invited many;</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and at the dinner hour he sent his slave to say to those who had been invited, ‘Come; for everything is ready now.’</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But they all alike began to make excuses. The first one said to him, ‘I have bought a piece of land and I need to go out and look at it; please consider me excused.’</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Another one said, ‘I have bought five yoke of oxen, and I am going to try them out; please consider me excused.’</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Another one said, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25574N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25574N\"></sup>I have married a wife, and for that reason I cannot come.’</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the slave came <i>back</i> and reported this to his master. Then the head of the household became angry and said to his slave, ‘Go out at once into the streets and lanes of the city and bring in here the poor and crippled and blind and lame.’</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And the slave said, ‘Master, what you commanded has been done, and still there is room.’</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the master said to the slave, ‘Go out into the highways and along the hedges, and compel <i>them</i> to come in, so that my house may be filled.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For I tell you, none of those men who were invited shall taste of my dinner.’”</span>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now large crowds were going along with Him; and He turned and said to them,",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25580O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25580O\"></sup>If anyone comes to Me, and does not hate his own father and mother and wife and children and brothers and sisters, yes, and even his own life, he cannot be My disciple.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Whoever does not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25581P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25581P\"></sup>carry his own cross and come after Me cannot be My disciple.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>For which one of you, when he wants to build a tower, does not first sit down and calculate the cost to see if he has enough to complete it?</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Otherwise, when he has laid a foundation and is not able to finish, all who observe it begin to ridicule him,</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>saying, ‘This man began to build and was not able to finish.’</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Or what king, when he sets out to meet another king in battle, will not first sit down and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25585Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25585Q\"></sup>consider whether he is strong enough with ten thousand <i>men</i> to encounter the one coming against him with twenty thousand?</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Or else, while the other is still far away, he sends a delegation and asks for terms of peace.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So then, none of you can be My disciple who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25587R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25587R\"></sup>does not give up all his own possessions.</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Therefore, salt is good; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25588S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25588S\"></sup>if even salt has become tasteless, with what will it be seasoned?</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>It is useless either for the soil or for the manure pile; it is thrown out. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25589T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25589T\"></sup>He who has ears to hear, let him hear.”</span>"
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>Now all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25590A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25590A\"></sup>tax collectors and the sinners were coming near Him to listen to Him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Both the Pharisees and the scribes <i>began</i> to grumble, saying, “This man receives sinners and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25591B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25591B\"></sup>eats with them.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So He told them this parable, saying,",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25593C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25593C\"></sup>What man among you, if he has a hundred sheep and has lost one of them, does not leave the ninety-nine in the open pasture and go after the one which is lost until he finds it?</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When he has found it, he lays it on his shoulders, rejoicing.</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And when he comes home, he calls together his friends and his neighbors, saying to them, ‘Rejoice with me, for I have found my sheep which was lost!’</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I tell you that in the same way, there will be <i>more</i> joy in heaven over one sinner who repents than over ninety-nine righteous persons who need no repentance.</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Or what woman, if she has ten silver coins and loses one coin, does not light a lamp and sweep the house and search carefully until she finds it?</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When she has found it, she calls together her friends and neighbors, saying, ‘Rejoice with me, for I have found the coin which I had lost!’</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In the same way, I tell you, there is joy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25599D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25599D\"></sup>in the presence of the angels of God over one sinner who repents.”</span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And He said, <span class=\"woj\">“A man had two sons.</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The younger of them said to his father, ‘Father, give me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25601E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25601E\"></sup>the share of the estate that falls to me.’ So he divided his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25601F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25601F\"></sup>wealth between them.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And not many days later, the younger son gathered everything together and went on a journey into a distant country, and there he squandered his estate with loose living.</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now when he had spent everything, a severe famine occurred in that country, and he began to be impoverished.</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So he went and hired himself out to one of the citizens of that country, and he sent him into his fields to feed swine.</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he would have gladly filled his stomach with the pods that the swine were eating, and no one was giving <i>anything</i> to him.</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But when he came to his senses, he said, ‘How many of my father’s hired men have more than enough bread, but I am dying here with hunger!</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I will get up and go to my father, and will say to him, “Father, I have sinned against heaven, and in your sight;</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I am no longer worthy to be called your son; make me as one of your hired men.”’</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So he got up and came to his father. But while he was still a long way off, his father saw him and felt compassion <i>for him</i>, and ran and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25609G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25609G\"></sup>embraced him and kissed him.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the son said to him, ‘Father, I have sinned against heaven and in your sight; I am no longer worthy to be called your son.’</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the father said to his slaves, ‘Quickly bring out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25611H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25611H\"></sup>the best robe and put it on him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25611I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25611I\"></sup>put a ring on his hand and sandals on his feet;</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and bring the fattened calf, kill it, and let us eat and celebrate;</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>for this son of mine was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25613J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25613J\"></sup>dead and has come to life again; he was lost and has been found.’ And they began to celebrate.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Now his older son was in the field, and when he came and approached the house, he heard music and dancing.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And he summoned one of the servants and <i>began</i> inquiring what these things could be.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And he said to him, ‘Your brother has come, and your father has killed the fattened calf because he has received him back safe and sound.’</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But he became angry and was not willing to go in; and his father came out and <i>began</i> pleading with him.</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But he answered and said to his father, ‘Look! For so many years I have been serving you and I have never neglected a command of yours; and <i>yet</i> you have never given me a young goat, so that I might celebrate with my friends;</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>but when this son of yours came, who has devoured your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25619K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25619K\"></sup>wealth with prostitutes, you killed the fattened calf for him.’</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And he said to him, ‘Son, you have always been with me, and all that is mine is yours.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But we had to celebrate and rejoice, for this brother of yours was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25621L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25621L\"></sup>dead and <i>has begun</i> to live, and <i>was</i> lost and has been found.’”</span>"
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>Now He was also saying to the disciples, <span class=\"woj\">“There was a rich man who had a manager, and this <i>manager</i> was reported to him as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25622A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25622A\"></sup>squandering his possessions.</span>",
			"2": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he called him and said to him, ‘What is this I hear about you? Give an accounting of your management, for you can no longer be manager.’</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The manager said to himself, ‘What shall I do, since my master is taking the management away from me? I am not strong enough to dig; I am ashamed to beg.</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I know what I shall do, so that when I am removed from the management people will welcome me into their homes.’</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he summoned each one of his master’s debtors, and he <i>began</i> saying to the first, ‘How much do you owe my master?’</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he said, ‘A hundred measures of oil.’ And he said to him, ‘Take your bill, and sit down quickly and write fifty.’</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then he said to another, ‘And how much do you owe?’ And he said, ‘A hundred measures of wheat.’ He *said to him, ‘Take your bill, and write eighty.’</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And his master praised the unrighteous manager because he had acted shrewdly; for the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25629B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25629B\"></sup>this age are more shrewd in relation to their own kind than the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25629C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25629C\"></sup>sons of light.</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And I say to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25630D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25630D\"></sup>make friends for yourselves by means of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25630E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25630E\"></sup>wealth of unrighteousness, so that when it fails, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25630F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25630F\"></sup>they will receive you into the eternal dwellings.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25631G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25631G\"></sup>He who is faithful in a very little thing is faithful also in much; and he who is unrighteous in a very little thing is unrighteous also in much.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Therefore if you have not been faithful in the <i>use of</i> unrighteous <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25632H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25632H\"></sup>wealth, who will entrust the true <i>riches</i> to you?</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And if you have not been faithful in <i>the use of</i> that which is another’s, who will give you that which is your own?</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25634I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25634I\"></sup>No servant can serve two masters; for either he will hate the one and love the other, or else he will be devoted to one and despise the other. You cannot serve God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25634J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25634J\"></sup>wealth.”</span>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now the Pharisees, who were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25635K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25635K\"></sup>lovers of money, were listening to all these things and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25635L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25635L\"></sup>were scoffing at Him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“You are those who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25636M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25636M\"></sup>justify yourselves in the sight of men, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25636N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25636N\"></sup>God knows your hearts; for that which is highly esteemed among men is detestable in the sight of God.</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25637O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25637O\"></sup>The Law and the Prophets <i>were proclaimed</i> until John; since that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25637P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25637P\"></sup>the gospel of the kingdom of God has been preached, and everyone is forcing his way into it.</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25638Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25638Q\"></sup>But it is easier for heaven and earth to pass away than for one stroke of a letter of the Law to fail.</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25639R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25639R\"></sup>Everyone who divorces his wife and marries another commits adultery, and he who marries one who is divorced from a husband commits adultery.</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Now there was a rich man, and he habitually dressed in purple and fine linen, joyously living in splendor every day.</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And a poor man named Lazarus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25641S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25641S\"></sup>was laid at his gate, covered with sores,</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and longing to be fed with the <i>crumbs</i> which were falling from the rich man’s table; besides, even the dogs were coming and licking his sores.</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now the poor man died and was carried away by the angels to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25643T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25643T\"></sup>Abraham’s bosom; and the rich man also died and was buried.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25644U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25644U\"></sup>Hades he lifted up his eyes, being in torment, and *saw Abraham far away and Lazarus in his bosom.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And he cried out and said, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25645V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25645V\"></sup>Father Abraham, have mercy on me, and send Lazarus so that he may dip the tip of his finger in water and cool off my tongue, for I am in agony in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25645W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25645W\"></sup>this flame.’</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But Abraham said, ‘Child, remember that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25646X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25646X\"></sup>during your life you received your good things, and likewise Lazarus bad things; but now he is being comforted here, and you are in agony.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And besides all this, between us and you there is a great chasm fixed, so that those who wish to come over from here to you will not be able, and <i>that</i> none may cross over from there to us.’</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And he said, ‘Then I beg you, father, that you send him to my father’s house—</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>for I have five brothers—in order that he may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25649Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25649Y\"></sup>warn them, so that they will not also come to this place of torment.’</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But Abraham *said, ‘They have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25650Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25650Z\"></sup>Moses and the Prophets; let them hear them.’</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But he said, ‘No, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25651AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25651AA\"></sup>father Abraham, but if someone goes to them from the dead, they will repent!’</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But he said to him, ‘If they do not listen to Moses and the Prophets, they will not be persuaded even if someone rises from the dead.’”</span>"
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>He said to His disciples, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25653A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25653A\"></sup>It is inevitable that stumbling blocks come, but woe to him through whom they come!</span>",
			"2": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25654B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25654B\"></sup>It would be better for him if a millstone were hung around his neck and he were thrown into the sea, than that he would cause one of these little ones to stumble.</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Be on your guard! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25655C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25655C\"></sup>If your brother sins, rebuke him; and if he repents, forgive him.</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And if he sins against you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25656D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25656D\"></sup>seven times a day, and returns to you seven times, saying, ‘I repent,’ forgive him.”</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25657E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25657E\"></sup>The apostles said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25657F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25657F\"></sup>the Lord, “Increase our faith!”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25658G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25658G\"></sup>the Lord said, <span class=\"woj\">“If you had faith like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25658H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25658H\"></sup>a mustard seed, you would say to this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25658I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25658I\"></sup>mulberry tree, ‘Be uprooted and be planted in the sea’; and it would obey you.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Which of you, having a slave plowing or tending sheep, will say to him when he has come in from the field, ‘Come immediately and sit down to eat’?</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But will he not say to him, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25660J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25660J\"></sup>Prepare something for me to eat, and <i>properly</i> clothe yourself and serve me while I eat and drink; and afterward you may eat and drink’?</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He does not thank the slave because he did the things which were commanded, does he?</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So you too, when you do all the things which are commanded you, say, ‘We are unworthy slaves; we have done <i>only</i> that which we ought to have done.’”</span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>While He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25663K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25663K\"></sup>on the way to Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25663L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25663L\"></sup>He was passing between Samaria and Galilee.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>As He entered a village, ten leprous men who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25664M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25664M\"></sup>stood at a distance met Him;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and they raised their voices, saying, “Jesus, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25665N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25665N\"></sup>Master, have mercy on us!”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When He saw them, He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25666O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25666O\"></sup>Go and show yourselves to the priests.”</span> And as they were going, they were cleansed.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now one of them, when he saw that he had been healed, turned back, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25667P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25667P\"></sup>glorifying God with a loud voice,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and he fell on his face at His feet, giving thanks to Him. And he was a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25668Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25668Q\"></sup>Samaritan.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Jesus answered and said, <span class=\"woj\">“Were there not ten cleansed? But the nine—where are they?</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Was no one found who returned to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25670R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25670R\"></sup>give glory to God, except this foreigner?”</span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And He said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Stand up and go; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25671S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25671S\"></sup>your faith has made you well.”</span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now having been questioned by the Pharisees <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25672T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25672T\"></sup>as to when the kingdom of God was coming, He answered them and said, <span class=\"woj\">“The kingdom of God is not coming with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25672U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25672U\"></sup>signs to be observed;</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>nor will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25673V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25673V\"></sup>they say, ‘Look, here <i>it is</i>!’ or, ‘There <i>it is</i>!’ For behold, the kingdom of God is in your midst.”</span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And He said to the disciples, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25674W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25674W\"></sup>The days will come when you will long to see one of the days of the Son of Man, and you will not see it.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25675X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25675X\"></sup>They will say to you, ‘Look there! Look here!’ Do not go away, and do not run after <i>them</i>.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25676Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25676Y\"></sup>For just like the lightning, when it flashes out of one part of the sky, shines to the other part of the sky, so will the Son of Man be in His day.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25677Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25677Z\"></sup>But first He must suffer many things and be rejected by this generation.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25678AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25678AA\"></sup>And just as it happened <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25678AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25678AB\"></sup>in the days of Noah, so it will be also in the days of the Son of Man:</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>they were eating, they were drinking, they were marrying, they were being given in marriage, until the day that Noah entered the ark, and the flood came and destroyed them all.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>It was the same as happened in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25680AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25680AC\"></sup>the days of Lot: they were eating, they were drinking, they were buying, they were selling, they were planting, they were building;</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>but on the day that Lot went out from Sodom it rained fire and brimstone from heaven and destroyed them all.</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>It will be just the same on the day that the Son of Man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25682AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25682AD\"></sup>is revealed.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>On that day, the one who is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25683AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25683AE\"></sup>on the housetop and whose goods are in the house must not go down to take them out; and likewise the one who is in the field must not turn back.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25684AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25684AF\"></sup>Remember Lot’s wife.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25685AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25685AG\"></sup>Whoever seeks to keep his life will lose it, and whoever loses <i>his life</i> will preserve it.</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>I tell you, on that night there will be two in one bed; one will be taken and the other will be left.</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25687AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25687AH\"></sup>There will be two women grinding at the same place; one will be taken and the other will be left.</span>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>[<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25688AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25688AI\"></sup>Two men will be in the field; one will be taken and the other will be left.”</span>]",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And answering they *said to Him, “Where, Lord?” And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25689AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25689AJ\"></sup>Where the body <i>is</i>, there also the vultures will be gathered.”</span>"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Now He was telling them a parable to show that at all times they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25690A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25690A\"></sup>ought to pray and not to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25690B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25690B\"></sup>lose heart,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>saying, <span class=\"woj\">“In a certain city there was a judge who did not fear God and did not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25691C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25691C\"></sup>respect man.</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>There was a widow in that city, and she kept coming to him, saying, ‘Give me legal protection from my opponent.’</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For a while he was unwilling; but afterward he said to himself, ‘Even though I do not fear God nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25693D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25693D\"></sup>respect man,</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25694E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25694E\"></sup>because this widow bothers me, I will give her legal protection, otherwise by continually coming she will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25694F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25694F\"></sup>wear me out.’”</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25695G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25695G\"></sup>the Lord said, <span class=\"woj\">“Hear what the unrighteous judge *said;</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>now, will not God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25696H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25696H\"></sup>bring about justice for His <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25696I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25696I\"></sup>elect who cry to Him day and night, and will He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25696J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25696J\"></sup>delay long over them?</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I tell you that He will bring about justice for them quickly. However, when the Son of Man comes, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25697K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25697K\"></sup>will He find faith on the earth?”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And He also told this parable to some people who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25698L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25698L\"></sup>trusted in themselves that they were righteous, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25698M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25698M\"></sup>viewed others with contempt:",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Two men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25699N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25699N\"></sup>went up into the temple to pray, one a Pharisee and the other a tax collector.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The Pharisee <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25700O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25700O\"></sup>stood and was praying this to himself: ‘God, I thank You that I am not like other people: swindlers, unjust, adulterers, or even like this tax collector.</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25701P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25701P\"></sup>fast twice a week; I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25701Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25701Q\"></sup>pay tithes of all that I get.’</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But the tax collector, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25702R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25702R\"></sup>standing some distance away, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25702S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25702S\"></sup>was even unwilling to lift up his eyes to heaven, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25702T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25702T\"></sup>was beating his breast, saying, ‘God, be merciful to me, the sinner!’</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I tell you, this man went to his house justified rather than the other; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25703U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25703U\"></sup>for everyone who exalts himself will be humbled, but he who humbles himself will be exalted.”</span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25704V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25704V\"></sup>And they were bringing even their babies to Him so that He would touch them, but when the disciples saw it, they <i>began</i> rebuking them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But Jesus called for them, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“Permit the children to come to Me, and do not hinder them, for the kingdom of God belongs to such as these.</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Truly I say to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25706W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25706W\"></sup>whoever does not receive the kingdom of God like a child will not enter it <i>at all</i>.”</span>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25707X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25707X\"></sup>A ruler questioned Him, saying, “Good Teacher, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Why do you call Me good? No one is good except God alone.</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You know the commandments, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25709Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25709Y\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Do not commit adultery, Do not murder, Do not steal, Do not bear false witness, Honor your father and mother</span>.’”</span>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And he said, “All these things I have kept from <i>my</i> youth.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When Jesus heard <i>this</i>, He said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“One thing you still lack; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25711Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25711Z\"></sup>sell all that you possess and distribute it to the poor, and you shall have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25711AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25711AA\"></sup>treasure in heaven; and come, follow Me.”</span>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But when he had heard these things, he became very sad, for he was extremely rich.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Jesus looked at him and said, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25713AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25713AB\"></sup>How hard it is for those who are wealthy to enter the kingdom of God!</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25714AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25714AC\"></sup>it is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle than for a rich man to enter the kingdom of God.”</span>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They who heard it said, “Then who can be saved?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But He said, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25716AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25716AD\"></sup>The things that are impossible with people are possible with God.”</span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Peter said, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25717AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25717AE\"></sup>we have left our own <i>homes</i> and followed You.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Truly I say to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25718AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25718AF\"></sup>there is no one who has left house or wife or brothers or parents or children, for the sake of the kingdom of God,</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>who will not receive many times as much at this time and in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25719AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25719AG\"></sup>the age to come, eternal life.”</span>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25720AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25720AH\"></sup>Then He took the twelve aside and said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25720AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25720AI\"></sup>we are going up to Jerusalem, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25720AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25720AJ\"></sup>all things which are written through the prophets about the Son of Man will be accomplished.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25721AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25721AK\"></sup>For He will be handed over to the Gentiles, and will be mocked and mistreated and spit upon,</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>and after they have scourged Him, they will kill Him; and the third day He will rise again.”</span>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25723AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25723AL\"></sup>the disciples understood none of these things, and <i>the meaning of</i> this statement was hidden from them, and they did not comprehend the things that were said.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25724AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25724AM\"></sup>As <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25724AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25724AN\"></sup>Jesus was approaching Jericho, a blind man was sitting by the road begging.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Now hearing a crowd going by, he <i>began</i> to inquire what this was.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>They told him that Jesus of Nazareth was passing by.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And he called out, saying, “Jesus, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25727AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25727AO\"></sup>Son of David, have mercy on me!”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Those who led the way were sternly telling him to be quiet; but he kept crying out all the more, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25728AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25728AP\"></sup>Son of David, have mercy on me!”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And Jesus stopped and commanded that he be brought to Him; and when he came near, He questioned him,",
			"41": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“What do you want Me to do for you?”</span> And he said, “Lord, <i>I want</i> to regain my sight!”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Receive your sight; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25731AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25731AQ\"></sup>your faith has made you well.”</span>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Immediately he regained his sight and <i>began</i> following Him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25732AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25732AR\"></sup>glorifying God; and when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25732AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25732AS\"></sup>all the people saw it, they gave praise to God."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25733A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25733A\"></sup>entered Jericho and was passing through.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And there was a man called by the name of Zaccheus; he was a chief tax collector and he was rich.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Zaccheus was trying to see who Jesus was, and was unable because of the crowd, for he was small in stature.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So he ran on ahead and climbed up into a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25736B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25736B\"></sup>sycamore tree in order to see Him, for He was about to pass through that way.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When Jesus came to the place, He looked up and said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Zaccheus, hurry and come down, for today I must stay at your house.”</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he hurried and came down and received Him gladly.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When they saw it, they all <i>began</i> to grumble, saying, “He has gone to be the guest of a man who is a sinner.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Zaccheus stopped and said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25740C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25740C\"></sup>the Lord, “Behold, Lord, half of my possessions I will give to the poor, and if I have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25740D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25740D\"></sup>defrauded anyone of anything, I will give back <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25740E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25740E\"></sup>four times as much.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Today salvation has come to this house, because he, too, is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25741F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25741F\"></sup>a son of Abraham.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25742G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25742G\"></sup>the Son of Man has come to seek and to save that which was lost.”</span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>While they were listening to these things, Jesus went on to tell a parable, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25743H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25743H\"></sup>He was near Jerusalem, and they supposed that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25743I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25743I\"></sup>the kingdom of God was going to appear immediately.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So He said, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25744J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25744J\"></sup>A nobleman went to a distant country to receive a kingdom for himself, and <i>then</i> return.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And he called ten of his slaves, and gave them ten minas and said to them, ‘Do business <i>with this</i> until I come <i>back</i>.’</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But his citizens hated him and sent a delegation after him, saying, ‘We do not want this man to reign over us.’</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When he returned, after receiving the kingdom, he ordered that these slaves, to whom he had given the money, be called to him so that he might know what business they had done.</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The first appeared, saying, ‘Master, your mina has made ten minas more.’</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he said to him, ‘Well done, good slave, because you have been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25749K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25749K\"></sup>faithful in a very little thing, you are to be in authority over ten cities.’</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The second came, saying, ‘Your mina, master, has made five minas.’</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he said to him also, ‘And you are to be over five cities.’</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Another came, saying, ‘Master, here is your mina, which I kept put away in a handkerchief;</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>for I was afraid of you, because you are an exacting man; you take up what you did not lay down and reap what you did not sow.’</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He *said to him, ‘By your own words I will judge you, you worthless slave. Did you know that I am an exacting man, taking up what I did not lay down and reaping what I did not sow?</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then why did you not put my money in the bank, and having come, I would have collected it with interest?’</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then he said to the bystanders, ‘Take the mina away from him and give it to the one who has the ten minas.’</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And they said to him, ‘Master, he has ten minas <i>already</i>.’</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25758L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25758L\"></sup>I tell you that to everyone who has, more shall be given, but from the one who does not have, even what he does have shall be taken away.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25759M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25759M\"></sup>these enemies of mine, who did not want me to reign over them, bring them here and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25759N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25759N\"></sup>slay them in my presence.”</span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>After He had said these things, He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25760O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25760O\"></sup>was going on ahead, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25760P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25760P\"></sup>going up to Jerusalem.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25761Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25761Q\"></sup>When He approached Bethphage and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25761R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25761R\"></sup>Bethany, near the mount that is called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25761S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25761S\"></sup>Olivet, He sent two of the disciples,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>saying, <span class=\"woj\">“Go into the village ahead of <i>you</i>; there, as you enter, you will find a colt tied on which no one yet has ever sat; untie it and bring it <i>here</i>.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>If anyone asks you, ‘Why are you untying it?’ you shall say, ‘The Lord has need of it.’”</span>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So those who were sent went away and found it just as He had told them.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>As they were untying the colt, its owners said to them, “Why are you untying the colt?”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>They said, “The Lord has need of it.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>They brought it to Jesus, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25767T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25767T\"></sup>and they threw their coats on the colt and put Jesus <i>on it</i>.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>As He was going, they were spreading their coats on the road.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>As soon as He was approaching, near the descent of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25769U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25769U\"></sup>the Mount of Olives, the whole crowd of the disciples began to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25769V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25769V\"></sup>praise God joyfully with a loud voice for all the miracles which they had seen,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>shouting:“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25770W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25770W\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Blessed is the</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25770X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25770X\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">King who comes in the name of the Lord</span>;Peace in heaven and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25770Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25770Y\"></sup>glory in the highest!”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25771Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25771Z\"></sup>Some of the Pharisees in the crowd said to Him, “Teacher, rebuke Your disciples.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>But Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“I tell you, if these become silent, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25772AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25772AA\"></sup>the stones will cry out!”</span>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>When He approached <i>Jerusalem</i>, He saw the city and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25773AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25773AB\"></sup>wept over it,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>saying, <span class=\"woj\">“If you had known in this day, even you, the things which make for peace! But now they have been hidden from your eyes.</span>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>For the days will come upon you when your enemies will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25775AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25775AC\"></sup>throw up a barricade against you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25775AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25775AD\"></sup>surround you and hem you in on every side,</span>",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>and they will level you to the ground and your children within you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25776AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25776AE\"></sup>they will not leave in you one stone upon another, because you did not recognize <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25776AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25776AF\"></sup>the time of your visitation.”</span>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25777AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25777AG\"></sup>Jesus entered the temple and began to drive out those who were selling,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>saying to them, <span class=\"woj\">“It is written, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25778AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25778AH\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">And My house shall be a house of prayer</span>,’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25778AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25778AI\"></sup>but you have made it a <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">robbers</span>’ <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">den</span>.”</span>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25779AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25779AJ\"></sup>He was teaching daily in the temple; but the chief priests and the scribes and the leading men among the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25779AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25779AK\"></sup>were trying to destroy Him,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>and they could not find anything that they might do, for all the people were hanging on to every word He said."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25781A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25781A\"></sup>On one of the days while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25781B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25781B\"></sup>He was teaching the people in the temple and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25781C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25781C\"></sup>preaching the gospel, the chief priests and the scribes with the elders <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25781D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25781D\"></sup>confronted <i>Him</i>,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and they spoke, saying to Him, “Tell us by what authority You are doing these things, or who is the one who gave You this authority?”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jesus answered and said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“I will also ask you a question, and you tell Me:</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Was the baptism of John from heaven or from men?”</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They reasoned among themselves, saying, “If we say, ‘From heaven,’ He will say, ‘Why did you not believe him?’",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But if we say, ‘From men,’ all the people will stone us to death, for they are convinced that John was a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25786E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25786E\"></sup>prophet.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So they answered that they did not know where <i>it came</i> from.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Nor will I tell you by what authority I do these things.”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25789F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25789F\"></sup>And He began to tell the people this parable: <span class=\"woj\">“A man planted a vineyard and rented it out to vine-growers, and went on a journey for a long time.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>At the <i>harvest</i> time he sent a slave to the vine-growers, so that they would give him <i>some</i> of the produce of the vineyard; but the vine-growers beat him and sent him away empty-handed.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he proceeded to send another slave; and they beat him also and treated him shamefully and sent him away empty-handed.</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he proceeded to send a third; and this one also they wounded and cast out.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The owner of the vineyard said, ‘What shall I do? I will send my beloved son; perhaps they will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25793G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25793G\"></sup>respect him.’</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But when the vine-growers saw him, they reasoned with one another, saying, ‘This is the heir; let us kill him so that the inheritance will be ours.’</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So they threw him out of the vineyard and killed him. What, then, will the owner of the vineyard do to them?</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He will come and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25796H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25796H\"></sup>destroy these vine-growers and will give the vineyard to others.”</span> When they heard it, they said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25796I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25796I\"></sup>May it never be!”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But Jesus looked at them and said, <span class=\"woj\">“What then is this that is written:</span><span class=\"woj\">‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25797J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25797J\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">The stone which the builders rejected</span>,</span><span class=\"woj\"><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">This became</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25797K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25797K\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">the chief corner</span> <i>stone</i>’?</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25798L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25798L\"></sup>Everyone who falls on that stone will be broken to pieces; but on whomever it falls, it will scatter him like dust.”</span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The scribes and the chief priests <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25799M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25799M\"></sup>tried to lay hands on Him that very hour, and they feared the people; for they understood that He spoke this parable against them.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25800N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25800N\"></sup>So they watched Him, and sent spies who pretended to be righteous, in order <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25800O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25800O\"></sup>that they might catch Him in some statement, so that they <i>could</i> deliver Him to the rule and the authority of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25800P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25800P\"></sup>the governor.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They questioned Him, saying, “Teacher, we know that You speak and teach correctly, and You are not partial to any, but teach the way of God in truth.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Is it lawful for us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25802Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25802Q\"></sup>to pay taxes to Caesar, or not?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But He detected their trickery and said to them,",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Show Me a denarius. Whose likeness and inscription does it have?”</span> They said, “Caesar’s.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25805R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25805R\"></sup>render to Caesar the things that are Caesar’s, and to God the things that are God’s.”</span>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And they were unable to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25806S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25806S\"></sup>catch Him in a saying in the presence of the people; and being amazed at His answer, they became silent.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25807T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25807T\"></sup>Now there came to Him some of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25807U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25807U\"></sup>Sadducees (who say that there is no resurrection),",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and they questioned Him, saying, “Teacher, Moses wrote for us that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25808V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25808V\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">if a man’s brother dies</span>, having a wife, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">and he is childless, his brother should</span> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">marry the wife and raise up children to his brother</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now there were seven brothers; and the first took a wife and died childless;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and the second",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and the third married her; and in the same way all seven died, leaving no children.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Finally the woman died also.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>In the resurrection therefore, which one’s wife will she be? For all seven had married her.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25814W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25814W\"></sup>this age marry and are given in marriage,</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>but those who are considered worthy to attain to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25815X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25815X\"></sup>that age and the resurrection from the dead, neither marry nor are given in marriage;</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>for they cannot even die anymore, because they are like angels, and are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25816Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25816Y\"></sup>sons of God, being sons of the resurrection.</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>But that the dead are raised, even Moses showed, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25817Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25817Z\"></sup>the <i>passage about the burning</i> bush, where he calls the Lord <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25817AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25817AA\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob</span>.</span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25818AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25818AB\"></sup>Now He is not the God of the dead but of the living; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25818AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25818AC\"></sup>all live to Him.”</span>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Some of the scribes answered and said, “Teacher, You have spoken well.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25820AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25820AD\"></sup>they did not have courage to question Him any longer about anything.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25821AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25821AE\"></sup>Then He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“How <i>is it that</i> they say the Christ is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25821AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25821AF\"></sup>David’s son?</span>",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>For David himself says in the book of Psalms,</span><span class=\"woj\">‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25822AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25822AG\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">The Lord said to my Lord</span>,</span><span class=\"woj\">“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Sit at My right hand</span>,</span>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25823AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25823AH\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Until I make Your enemies a footstool for Your feet</span>.”’</span>",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Therefore David calls Him ‘Lord,’ and how is He his son?”</span>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25825AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25825AI\"></sup>And while all the people were listening, He said to the disciples,",
			"46": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“Beware of the scribes, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25826AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25826AJ\"></sup>who like to walk around in long robes, and love respectful greetings in the market places, and chief seats in the synagogues and places of honor at banquets,</span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>who devour widows’ houses, and for appearance’s sake offer long prayers. These will receive greater condemnation.”</span>"
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25828A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25828A\"></sup>And He looked up and saw the rich putting their gifts into the treasury.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And He saw a poor widow putting in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25829B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25829B\"></sup>two small copper coins.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And He said, <span class=\"woj\">“Truly I say to you, this poor widow put in more than all <i>of them</i>;</span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>for they all out of their surplus put into the offering; but she out of her poverty put in all that she had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25831C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25831C\"></sup>to live on.”</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25832D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25832D\"></sup>And while some were talking about the temple, that it was adorned with beautiful stones and votive gifts, He said,",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“<i>As for</i> these things which you are looking at, the days will come in which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25833E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25833E\"></sup>there will not be left one stone upon another which will not be torn down.”</span>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They questioned Him, saying, “Teacher, when therefore will these things happen? And what <i>will be</i> the sign when these things are about to take place?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And He said, <span class=\"woj\">“See to it that you are not misled; for many will come in My name, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25835F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25835F\"></sup>I am <i>He</i>,’ and, ‘The time is near.’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25835G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25835G\"></sup>Do not go after them.</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When you hear of wars and disturbances, do not be terrified; for these things must take place first, but the end <i>does</i> not <i>follow</i> immediately.”</span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then He continued by saying to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Nation will rise against nation and kingdom against kingdom,</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and there will be great earthquakes, and in various places plagues and famines; and there will be terrors and great signs from heaven.</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“But before all these things, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25839H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25839H\"></sup>they will lay their hands on you and will persecute you, delivering you to the synagogues and prisons, bringing you before kings and governors for My name’s sake.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25840I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25840I\"></sup>It will lead to an opportunity for your testimony.</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25841J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25841J\"></sup>So make up your minds not to prepare beforehand to defend yourselves;</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25842K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25842K\"></sup>I will give you utterance and wisdom which none of your opponents will be able to resist or refute.</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But you will be betrayed even by parents and brothers and relatives and friends, and they will put <i>some</i> of you to death,</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and you will be hated by all because of My name.</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25845L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25845L\"></sup>not a hair of your head will perish.</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25846M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25846M\"></sup>By your endurance you will gain your lives.</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“But when you see Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25847N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25847N\"></sup>surrounded by armies, then recognize that her desolation is near.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then those who are in Judea must flee to the mountains, and those who are in the midst of the city must leave, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25848O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25848O\"></sup>those who are in the country must not enter the city;</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>because these are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25849P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25849P\"></sup>days of vengeance, so that all things which are written will be fulfilled.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Woe to those who are pregnant and to those who are nursing babies in those days; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25850Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25850Q\"></sup>there will be great distress upon the land and wrath to this people;</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and they will fall by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25851R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25851R\"></sup>the edge of the sword, and will be led captive into all the nations; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25851S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25851S\"></sup>Jerusalem will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25851T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25851T\"></sup>trampled under foot by the Gentiles until <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25851U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25851U\"></sup>the times of the Gentiles are fulfilled.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“There will be signs in sun and moon and stars, and on the earth dismay among nations, in perplexity at the roaring of the sea and the waves,</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>men fainting from fear and the expectation of the things which are coming upon the world; for the powers of the heavens will be shaken.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25854V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25854V\"></sup>Then they will see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25854W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25854W\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">the Son of Man coming in a cloud</span> with power and great glory.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But when these things begin to take place, straighten up and lift up your heads, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25855X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25855X\"></sup>your redemption is drawing near.”</span>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then He told them a parable: <span class=\"woj\">“Behold the fig tree and all the trees;</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>as soon as they put forth <i>leaves</i>, you see it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25857Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25857Y\"></sup>know for yourselves that summer is now near.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So you also, when you see these things happening, recognize that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25858Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25858Z\"></sup>the kingdom of God is near.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Truly I say to you, this generation will not pass away until all things take place.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25860AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25860AA\"></sup>Heaven and earth will pass away, but My words will not pass away.</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25861AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25861AB\"></sup>Be on guard, so that your hearts will not be weighted down with dissipation and drunkenness and the worries of life, and that day will not come on you suddenly like a trap;</span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>for it will come upon all those who dwell on the face of all the earth.</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25863AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25863AC\"></sup>keep on the alert at all times, praying that you may have strength to escape all these things that are about to take place, and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25863AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25863AD\"></sup>stand before the Son of Man.”</span>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Now during the day He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25864AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25864AE\"></sup>teaching in the temple, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25864AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25864AF\"></sup>at evening He would go out and spend the night on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25864AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25864AG\"></sup>the mount that is called Olivet.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And all the people would get up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25865AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25865AH\"></sup>early in the morning <i>to come</i> to Him in the temple to listen to Him."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25866A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25866A\"></sup>Now the Feast of Unleavened Bread, which is called the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25866B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25866B\"></sup>Passover, was approaching.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The chief priests and the scribes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25867C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25867C\"></sup>were seeking how they might put Him to death; for they were afraid of the people.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25868D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25868D\"></sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25868E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25868E\"></sup>Satan entered into Judas who was called Iscariot, belonging to the number of the twelve.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he went away and discussed with the chief priests and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25869F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25869F\"></sup>officers how he might betray Him to them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They were glad and agreed to give him money.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So he consented, and <i>began</i> seeking a good opportunity to betray Him to them apart from the crowd.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25872G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25872G\"></sup>Then came the <i>first</i> day of Unleavened Bread on which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25872H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25872H\"></sup>the Passover <i>lamb</i> had to be sacrificed.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Jesus sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25873I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25873I\"></sup>Peter and John, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“Go and prepare the Passover for us, so that we may eat it.”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They said to Him, “Where do You want us to prepare it?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“When you have entered the city, a man will meet you carrying a pitcher of water; follow him into the house that he enters.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And you shall say to the owner of the house, ‘The Teacher says to you, “Where is the guest room in which I may eat the Passover with My disciples?”’</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And he will show you a large, furnished upper room; prepare it there.”</span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And they left and found <i>everything</i> just as He had told them; and they prepared the Passover.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25879J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25879J\"></sup>When the hour had come, He reclined <i>at the table</i>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25879K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25879K\"></sup>the apostles with Him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“I have earnestly desired to eat this Passover with you before I suffer;</span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>for I say to you, I shall never again eat it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25881L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25881L\"></sup>until it is fulfilled in the kingdom of God.”</span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25882M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25882M\"></sup>And when He had taken a cup <i>and</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25882N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25882N\"></sup>given thanks, He said, <span class=\"woj\">“Take this and share it among yourselves;</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25883O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25883O\"></sup>I say to you, I will not drink of the fruit of the vine from now on until the kingdom of God comes.”</span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And when He had taken <i>some</i> bread <i>and</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25884P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25884P\"></sup>given thanks, He broke it and gave it to them, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“This is My body which is given for you; do this in remembrance of Me.”</span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And in the same way <i>He took</i> the cup after they had eaten, saying, <span class=\"woj\">“This cup which is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25885Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25885Q\"></sup>poured out for you is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25885R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25885R\"></sup>new covenant in My blood.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25886S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25886S\"></sup>But behold, the hand of the one betraying Me is with Mine on the table.</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For indeed, the Son of Man is going <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25887T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25887T\"></sup>as it has been determined; but woe to that man by whom He is betrayed!”</span>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And they began to discuss among themselves which one of them it might be who was going to do this thing.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And there arose also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25889U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25889U\"></sup>a dispute among them <i>as to</i> which one of them was regarded to be greatest.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25890V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25890V\"></sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“The kings of the Gentiles lord it over them; and those who have authority over them are called ‘Benefactors.’</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But <i>it is</i> not this way with you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25891W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25891W\"></sup>but the one who is the greatest among you must become like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25891X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25891X\"></sup>the youngest, and the leader like the servant.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25892Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25892Y\"></sup>who is greater, the one who reclines <i>at the table</i> or the one who serves? Is it not the one who reclines <i>at the table</i>? But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25892Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25892Z\"></sup>I am among you as the one who serves.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“You are those who have stood by Me in My <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25893AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25893AA\"></sup>trials;</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and just as My Father has granted Me a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25894AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25894AB\"></sup>kingdom, I grant you</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>that you may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25895AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25895AC\"></sup>eat and drink at My table in My <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25895AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25895AD\"></sup>kingdom, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25895AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25895AE\"></sup>you will sit on thrones judging the twelve tribes of Israel.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“Simon, Simon, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25896AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25896AF\"></sup>Satan has demanded <i>permission</i> to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25896AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25896AG\"></sup>sift you like wheat;</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>but I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25897AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25897AH\"></sup>have prayed for you, that your faith may not fail; and you, when once you have turned again, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25897AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25897AI\"></sup>strengthen your brothers.”</span>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25898AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25898AJ\"></sup>But he said to Him, “Lord, with You I am ready to go both to prison and to death!”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And He said, <span class=\"woj\">“I say to you, Peter, the rooster will not crow today until you have denied three times that you know Me.”</span>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25900AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25900AK\"></sup>When I sent you out without money belt and bag and sandals, you did not lack anything, did you?”</span> They said, “<i>No</i>, nothing.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“But now, whoever has a money belt is to take it along, likewise also a bag, and whoever has no sword is to sell his coat and buy one.</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>For I tell you that this which is written must be fulfilled in Me, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25902AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25902AL\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">And He was numbered with transgressors</span>’; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25902AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25902AM\"></sup>that which refers to Me has <i>its</i> fulfillment.”</span>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>They said, “Lord, look, here are two <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25903AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25903AN\"></sup>swords.” And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“It is enough.”</span>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25904AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25904AO\"></sup>And He came out and proceeded <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25904AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25904AP\"></sup>as was His custom to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25904AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25904AQ\"></sup>the Mount of Olives; and the disciples also followed Him.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25905AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25905AR\"></sup>When He arrived at the place, He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25905AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25905AS\"></sup>Pray that you may not enter into temptation.”</span>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And He withdrew from them about a stone’s throw, and He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25906AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25906AT\"></sup>knelt down and <i>began</i> to pray,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>saying, <span class=\"woj\">“Father, if You are willing, remove this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25907AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25907AU\"></sup>cup from Me; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25907AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25907AV\"></sup>yet not My will, but Yours be done.”</span>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Now an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25908AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25908AW\"></sup>angel from heaven appeared to Him, strengthening Him.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25909AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25909AX\"></sup>being in agony He was praying very fervently; and His sweat became like drops of blood, falling down upon the ground.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>When He rose from prayer, He came to the disciples and found them sleeping from sorrow,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>and said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Why are you sleeping? Get up and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25911AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25911AY\"></sup>pray that you may not enter into temptation.”</span>",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25912AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25912AZ\"></sup>While He was still speaking, behold, a crowd <i>came</i>, and the one called Judas, one of the twelve, was preceding them; and he approached Jesus to kiss Him.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>But Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Judas, are you betraying the Son of Man with a kiss?”</span>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>When those who were around Him saw what was going to happen, they said, “Lord, shall we strike with the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25914BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25914BA\"></sup>sword?”",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>And one of them struck the slave of the high priest and cut off his right ear.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>But Jesus answered and said, <span class=\"woj\">“Stop! No more of this.”</span> And He touched his ear and healed him.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Then Jesus said to the chief priests and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25917BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25917BB\"></sup>officers of the temple and elders who had come against Him, <span class=\"woj\">“Have you come out with swords and clubs <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25917BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25917BC\"></sup>as you would against a robber?</span>",
			"53": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>While I was with you daily in the temple, you did not lay hands on Me; but this hour and the power of darkness are yours.”</span>",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25919BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25919BD\"></sup>Having arrested Him, they led Him <i>away</i> and brought Him to the house of the high priest; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25919BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25919BE\"></sup>Peter was following at a distance.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25920BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25920BF\"></sup>After they had kindled a fire in the middle of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25920BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25920BG\"></sup>the courtyard and had sat down together, Peter was sitting among them.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>And a servant-girl, seeing him as he sat in the firelight and looking intently at him, said, “This man was with Him too.”",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>But he denied <i>it</i>, saying, “Woman, I do not know Him.”",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>A little later, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25923BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25923BH\"></sup>another saw him and said, “You are <i>one</i> of them too!” But Peter said, “Man, I am not!”",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>After about an hour had passed, another man <i>began</i> to insist, saying, “Certainly this man also was with Him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25924BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25924BI\"></sup>for he is a Galilean too.”",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>But Peter said, “Man, I do not know what you are talking about.” Immediately, while he was still speaking, a rooster crowed.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25926BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25926BJ\"></sup>The Lord turned and looked at Peter. And Peter remembered the word of the Lord, how He had told him, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25926BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25926BK\"></sup>Before a rooster crows today, you will deny Me three times.”</span>",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>And he went out and wept bitterly.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25928BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25928BL\"></sup>Now the men who were holding Jesus in custody were mocking Him and beating Him,",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>and they blindfolded Him and were asking Him, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25929BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25929BM\"></sup>Prophesy, who is the one who hit You?”",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>And they were saying many other things against Him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25930BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25930BN\"></sup>blaspheming.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25931BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25931BO\"></sup>When it was day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25931BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25931BP\"></sup>the Council of elders of the people assembled, both chief priests and scribes, and they led Him away to their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25931BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25931BQ\"></sup>council <i>chamber</i>, saying,",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25932BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25932BR\"></sup>If You are the Christ, tell us.” But He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“If I tell you, you will not believe;</span>",
			"68": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>and if I ask a question, you will not answer.</span>",
			"69": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25934BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25934BS\"></sup>But from now on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25934BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25934BT\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">the Son of Man will be seated at the right hand</span> of the power <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">of God</span>.”</span>",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>And they all said, “Are You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25935BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25935BU\"></sup>the Son of God, then?” And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25935BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25935BV\"></sup>Yes, I am.”</span>",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup>Then they said, “What further need do we have of testimony? For we have heard it ourselves from His own mouth.”"
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>Then the whole body of them got up and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25937A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25937A\"></sup>brought Him before Pilate.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25938B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25938B\"></sup>And they began to accuse Him, saying, “We found this man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25938C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25938C\"></sup>misleading our nation and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25938D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25938D\"></sup>forbidding to pay taxes to Caesar, and saying that He Himself is Christ, a King.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Pilate asked Him, saying, “Are You the King of the Jews?” And He answered him and said, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25939E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25939E\"></sup><i>It is as</i> you say.”</span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Pilate said to the chief priests and the crowds, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25940F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25940F\"></sup>I find no guilt in this man.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But they kept on insisting, saying, “He stirs up the people, teaching all over Judea, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25941G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25941G\"></sup>starting from Galilee even as far as this place.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Pilate heard it, he asked whether the man was a Galilean.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And when he learned that He belonged to Herod’s jurisdiction, he sent Him to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25943H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25943H\"></sup>Herod, who himself also was in Jerusalem at that time.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now Herod was very glad when he saw Jesus; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25944I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25944I\"></sup>he had wanted to see Him for a long time, because he had been hearing about Him and was hoping to see some sign performed by Him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And he questioned Him at some length; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25945J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25945J\"></sup>He answered him nothing.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the chief priests and the scribes were standing there, accusing Him vehemently.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Herod with his soldiers, after treating Him with contempt and mocking Him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25947K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25947K\"></sup>dressed Him in a gorgeous robe and sent Him back to Pilate.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25948L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25948L\"></sup>Herod and Pilate became friends with one another that very day; for before they had been enemies with each other.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Pilate summoned the chief priests and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25949M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25949M\"></sup>rulers and the people,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and said to them, “You brought this man to me as one who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25950N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25950N\"></sup>incites the people to rebellion, and behold, having examined Him before you, I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25950O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25950O\"></sup>have found no guilt in this man regarding the charges which you make against Him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>No, nor has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25951P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25951P\"></sup>Herod, for he sent Him back to us; and behold, nothing deserving death has been done by Him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Therefore I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25952Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25952Q\"></sup>punish Him and release Him.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>[Now he was obliged to release to them at the feast one prisoner.]",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But they cried out all together, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25954R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25954R\"></sup>Away with this man, and release for us Barabbas!”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>(He was one who had been thrown into prison for an insurrection made in the city, and for murder.)",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Pilate, wanting to release Jesus, addressed them again,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>but they kept on calling out, saying, “Crucify, crucify Him!”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And he said to them the third time, “Why, what evil has this man done? I have found in Him no guilt <i>demanding</i> death; therefore I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25958S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25958S\"></sup>punish Him and release Him.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But they were insistent, with loud voices asking that He be crucified. And their voices <i>began</i> to prevail.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Pilate pronounced sentence that their demand be granted.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And he released the man they were asking for who had been thrown into prison for insurrection and murder, but he delivered Jesus to their will.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25962T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25962T\"></sup>When they led Him away, they seized a man, Simon of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25962U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25962U\"></sup>Cyrene, coming in from the country, and placed on him the cross to carry behind Jesus.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And following Him was a large crowd of the people, and of women who were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25963V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25963V\"></sup>mourning and lamenting Him.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But Jesus turning to them said, <span class=\"woj\">“Daughters of Jerusalem, stop weeping for Me, but weep for yourselves and for your children.</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>For behold, the days are coming when they will say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25965W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25965W\"></sup>Blessed are the barren, and the wombs that never bore, and the breasts that never nursed.’</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then they will begin <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">to</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25966X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25966X\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">say to the mountains, ‘Fall on us,’ and to the hills, ‘Cover us</span>.’</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>For if they do these things when the tree is green, what will happen when it is dry?”</span>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25968Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25968Y\"></sup>Two others also, who were criminals, were being led away to be put to death with Him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25969Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25969Z\"></sup>When they came to the place called The Skull, there they crucified Him and the criminals, one on the right and the other on the left.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But Jesus was saying, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25970AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25970AA\"></sup>Father, forgive them; for they do not know what they are doing.”</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25970AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25970AB\"></sup>And they cast lots, dividing up His garments among themselves.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And the people stood by, looking on. And even the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25971AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25971AC\"></sup>rulers were sneering at Him, saying, “He saved others; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25971AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25971AD\"></sup>let Him save Himself if this is the Christ of God, His Chosen One.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The soldiers also mocked Him, coming up to Him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25972AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25972AE\"></sup>offering Him sour wine,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>and saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25973AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25973AF\"></sup>If You are the King of the Jews, save Yourself!”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Now there was also an inscription above Him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25974AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25974AG\"></sup>THIS IS THE KING OF THE JEWS.”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25975AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25975AH\"></sup>One of the criminals who were hanged <i>there</i> was hurling abuse at Him, saying, “Are You not the Christ? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25975AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25975AI\"></sup>Save Yourself and us!”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>But the other answered, and rebuking him said, “Do you not even fear God, since you are under the same sentence of condemnation?",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And we indeed <i>are suffering</i> justly, for we are receiving what we deserve for our deeds; but this man has done nothing wrong.”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And he was saying, “Jesus, remember me when You come in Your kingdom!”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And He said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Truly I say to you, today you shall be with Me in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25979AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25979AJ\"></sup>Paradise.”</span>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25980AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25980AK\"></sup>It was now about <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25980AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25980AL\"></sup>the sixth hour, and darkness fell over the whole land until the ninth hour,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>because the sun was obscured; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25981AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25981AM\"></sup>the veil of the temple was torn in two.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>And Jesus, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25982AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25982AN\"></sup>crying out with a loud voice, said, <span class=\"woj\">“Father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25982AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25982AO\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">into Your hands I commit My spirit</span>.”</span> Having said this, He breathed His last.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25983AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25983AP\"></sup>Now when the centurion saw what had happened, he <i>began</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25983AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25983AQ\"></sup>praising God, saying, “Certainly this man was innocent.”",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>And all the crowds who came together for this spectacle, when they observed what had happened, <i>began</i> to return, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25984AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25984AR\"></sup>beating their breasts.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25985AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25985AS\"></sup>And all His acquaintances and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25985AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25985AT\"></sup>the women who accompanied Him from Galilee were standing at a distance, seeing these things.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25986AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25986AU\"></sup>And a man named Joseph, who was a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25986AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25986AV\"></sup>member of the Council, a good and righteous man",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>(he had not consented to their plan and action), <i>a man</i> from Arimathea, a city of the Jews, who was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25987AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25987AW\"></sup>waiting for the kingdom of God;",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>this man went to Pilate and asked for the body of Jesus.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>And he took it down and wrapped it in a linen cloth, and laid Him in a tomb cut into the rock, where no one had ever lain.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>It was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25990AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25990AX\"></sup>the preparation day, and the Sabbath was about to begin.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25991AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25991AY\"></sup>the women who had come with Him out of Galilee followed, and saw the tomb and how His body was laid.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>Then they returned and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25992AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25992AZ\"></sup>prepared spices and perfumes.And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25992BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25992BA\"></sup>on the Sabbath they rested according to the commandment."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25993A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25993A\"></sup>But on the first day of the week, at early dawn, they came to the tomb bringing the spices which they had prepared.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And they found the stone rolled away from the tomb,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>but when they entered, they did not find the body of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25995B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25995B\"></sup>the Lord Jesus.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>While they were perplexed about this, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25996C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25996C\"></sup>two men suddenly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25996D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25996D\"></sup>stood near them in dazzling clothing;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and as <i>the women</i> were terrified and bowed their faces to the ground, <i>the men</i> said to them, “Why do you seek the living One among the dead?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He is not here, but He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25998E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25998E\"></sup>has risen. Remember how He spoke to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25998F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25998F\"></sup>while He was still in Galilee,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>saying that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25999G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25999G\"></sup>the Son of Man must be delivered into the hands of sinful men, and be crucified, and the third day rise again.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26000H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26000H\"></sup>they remembered His words,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and returned from the tomb and reported all these things to the eleven and to all the rest.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now they were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26002I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26002I\"></sup>Mary Magdalene and Joanna and Mary the <i>mother</i> of James; also the other women with them were telling these things to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26002J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26002J\"></sup>the apostles.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But these words appeared to them as nonsense, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26003K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26003K\"></sup>would not believe them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But Peter got up and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26004L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26004L\"></sup>ran to the tomb; stooping and looking in, he *saw the linen wrappings only; and he went away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26004M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26004M\"></sup>to his home, marveling at what had happened.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26005N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26005N\"></sup>two of them were going that very day to a village named Emmaus, which was about seven miles from Jerusalem.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And they were talking with each other about all these things which had taken place.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>While they were talking and discussing, Jesus Himself approached and <i>began</i> traveling with them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26008O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26008O\"></sup>their eyes were prevented from recognizing Him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“What are these words that you are exchanging with one another as you are walking?”</span> And they stood still, looking sad.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>One <i>of them</i>, named Cleopas, answered and said to Him, “Are You the only one visiting Jerusalem and unaware of the things which have happened here in these days?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“What things?”</span> And they said to Him, “The things about <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26011P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26011P\"></sup>Jesus the Nazarene, who was a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26011Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26011Q\"></sup>prophet mighty in deed and word in the sight of God and all the people,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and how the chief priests and our <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26012R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26012R\"></sup>rulers delivered Him to the sentence of death, and crucified Him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But we were hoping that it was He who was going to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26013S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26013S\"></sup>redeem Israel. Indeed, besides all this, it is the third day since these things happened.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But also some women among us amazed us. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26014T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26014T\"></sup>When they were at the tomb early in the morning,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and did not find His body, they came, saying that they had also seen a vision of angels who said that He was alive.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Some of those who were with us went to the tomb and found it just exactly as the women also had said; but Him they did not see.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“O foolish men and slow of heart to believe in all that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26017U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26017U\"></sup>the prophets have spoken!</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26018V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26018V\"></sup>Was it not necessary for the Christ to suffer these things and to enter into His glory?”</span>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then beginning with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26019W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26019W\"></sup>Moses and with all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26019X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26019X\"></sup>prophets, He explained to them the things concerning Himself in all the Scriptures.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And they approached the village where they were going, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26020Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26020Y\"></sup>He acted as though He were going farther.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But they urged Him, saying, “Stay with us, for it is <i>getting</i> toward evening, and the day is now nearly over.” So He went in to stay with them.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When He had reclined <i>at the table</i> with them, He took the bread and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26022Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26022Z\"></sup>blessed <i>it</i>, and breaking <i>it</i>, He <i>began</i> giving <i>it</i> to them.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26023AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26023AA\"></sup>eyes were opened and they recognized Him; and He vanished from their sight.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>They said to one another, “Were not our hearts burning within us while He was speaking to us on the road, while He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26024AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26024AB\"></sup>was explaining the Scriptures to us?”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And they got up that very hour and returned to Jerusalem, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26025AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26025AC\"></sup>found gathered together the eleven and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26025AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26025AD\"></sup>those who were with them,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26026AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26026AE\"></sup>The Lord has really risen and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26026AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26026AF\"></sup>has appeared to Simon.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>They <i>began</i> to relate their experiences on the road and how <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26027AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26027AG\"></sup>He was recognized by them in the breaking of the bread.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>While they were telling these things, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26028AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26028AH\"></sup>He Himself stood in their midst and *said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Peace be to you.”</span>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>But they were startled and frightened and thought that they were seeing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26029AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26029AI\"></sup>a spirit.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Why are you troubled, and why do doubts arise in your hearts?</span>",
			"39": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26031AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26031AJ\"></sup>See My hands and My feet, that it is I Myself; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26031AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26031AK\"></sup>touch Me and see, for a spirit does not have flesh and bones as you see that I have.”</span>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And when He had said this, He showed them His hands and His feet.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>While they still <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26033AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26033AL\"></sup>could not believe <i>it</i> because of their joy and amazement, He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26033AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26033AM\"></sup>Have you anything here to eat?”</span>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>They gave Him a piece of a broiled fish;",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>and He took it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26035AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26035AN\"></sup>ate <i>it</i> before them.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Now He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26036AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26036AO\"></sup>These are My words which I spoke to you while I was still with you, that all things which are written about Me in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26036AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26036AP\"></sup>Law of Moses and the Prophets and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26036AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26036AQ\"></sup>the Psalms must be fulfilled.”</span>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Then He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26037AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26037AR\"></sup>opened their minds to understand the Scriptures,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>and He said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26038AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26038AS\"></sup>Thus it is written, that the Christ would suffer and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26038AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26038AT\"></sup>rise again from the dead the third day,</span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>and that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26039AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26039AU\"></sup>repentance for forgiveness of sins would be proclaimed in His name to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26039AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26039AV\"></sup>all the nations, beginning from Jerusalem.</span>",
			"48": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>You are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26040AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26040AW\"></sup>witnesses of these things.</span>",
			"49": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>And behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26041AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26041AX\"></sup>I am sending forth the promise of My Father upon you; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26041AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26041AY\"></sup>you are to stay in the city until you are clothed with power from on high.”</span>",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>And He led them out as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26042AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26042AZ\"></sup>Bethany, and He lifted up His hands and blessed them.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>While He was blessing them, He parted from them and was carried up into heaven.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>And they, after worshiping Him, returned to Jerusalem with great joy,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>and were continually in the temple praising God."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;